WEBVTT

00:03.204 --> 00:06.471
              [¶¶¶]

00:32.466 --> 00:36.168
  [CATHY]: <i> PEOPLE HAVE AN IMAGE</i>
   <i> OF WHAT A GOOD MOTHER IS.</i>

00:36.170 --> 00:38.037
            <i> GOOD...</i>

00:38.039 --> 00:41.740
      <i> LIKE THE ONES WE SAW</i>
   <i> ON OUR FAVORITE TV SHOWS.</i>

00:41.742 --> 00:45.144
       <i> MOST LITTLE GIRLS</i>
    <i> LEARN HOW TO BE MOTHERS</i>

00:45.146 --> 00:47.546
       <i> FROM OUR MOTHERS,</i>

00:47.548 --> 00:51.216
          <i> HOW TO COOK</i>
       <i> FAVORITE MEALS...</i>

00:51.218 --> 00:53.185
     <i> HOW TO KISS BOO-BOOS.</i>

00:54.221 --> 00:55.454
         <i> AND WE EMBRACE</i>

00:55.456 --> 00:57.556
    <i> ALL THE WONDERFUL THINGS</i>
           <i> THEY DID.</i>

01:00.194 --> 01:03.729
   <i> AND VOW TO DO DIFFERENTLY</i>
     <i> ALL OF THEIR MISTAKES.</i>

01:05.132 --> 01:06.532
    [CHRIS]: HE'S REBUILT IT
       TO JUST LIKE IT WAS

01:06.534 --> 01:08.167
     BEFORE IT BURNED DOWN.

01:12.473 --> 01:14.606
              [¶¶¶]

01:14.608 --> 01:16.542
IT STILL
TERRIFIES ME.

01:16.544 --> 01:19.478
         THIS HOUSE HAS
    NO POWER OVER US, CATHY.

01:19.480 --> 01:22.748
WE'RE NOT MOTHER'S DRESDEN DOLLS
  LOCKED IN THE ATTIC ANYMORE.

01:24.085 --> 01:26.485
                        COME ON.

01:31.092 --> 01:34.226
              [¶¶¶]

01:51.479 --> 01:55.180
          <i> EVENTUALLY,</i>
      <i> LITTLE GIRLS GROW UP</i>

01:55.182 --> 01:58.217
<i>AND HAVE REAL, BEAUTIFUL BABIES</i>
          <i> OF OUR OWN.</i>

01:59.520 --> 02:03.188
     <i> AND WE FILL THEM WITH</i>
  <i> ALL OF OUR HOPES AND DREAMS,</i>

02:03.190 --> 02:05.624
   <i> AND SADNESS, AND FEARS...</i>

02:06.694 --> 02:08.827
        <i> AND NIGHTMARES.</i>

02:11.532 --> 02:13.866
              [¶¶¶]

02:22.243 --> 02:24.610
              [¶¶¶]

02:34.255 --> 02:38.457
              [¶¶¶]

02:38.459 --> 02:39.625
     [BUTLER KNOCKS ON DOOR]

02:39.627 --> 02:41.860
          DR. AND MRS. SHEFFIELD
          HAVE ARRIVED, SIR.

02:41.862 --> 02:44.196
       I'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.

02:47.401 --> 02:50.202
        THERE'S NO BLOOD
      LIKE FAMILY'S BLOOD.

02:50.204 --> 02:52.371
       AT THE END OF DAYS,

02:52.373 --> 02:55.340
        THEY ARE THE ONES
      THAT MATTER THE MOST.

02:56.644 --> 02:58.644
   ISN'T THAT RIGHT, MALCOLM?

03:00.414 --> 03:02.848
              [¶¶¶]

03:17.198 --> 03:18.830
      BART!

03:18.832 --> 03:22.401
OH, MY GOODNESS,
YOU LOOK SO HANDSOME.

03:22.403 --> 03:23.835
       YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL
         AS ALWAYS, MOM.

03:23.837 --> 03:25.337
               AND YOU WORE RED!

03:25.339 --> 03:26.672
               YOU ALWAYS KNOW
               HOW TO PLEASE ME.

03:26.674 --> 03:29.241
OH, SWEETIE.

03:29.243 --> 03:31.376
HERE, SAY HELLO
TO-- TO CHRIS.

03:31.378 --> 03:33.745
                   LOOKING GOOD,
                   OLD MAN.

03:33.747 --> 03:35.514
        THANK YOU, BART.

03:35.516 --> 03:36.915
   THE PLACE LOOKS WONDERFUL.

03:36.917 --> 03:39.251
            IT'S LIKE
     STEPPING BACK IN TIME.

03:39.253 --> 03:40.652
   WELL, I CAN ONLY HOPE THAT
    GREAT-GRANDFATHER MALCOLM

03:40.654 --> 03:41.787
        WOULD BE PLEASED.

03:41.789 --> 03:43.755
        I WAS METICULOUS
     ABOUT THE RESTORATION.

03:43.757 --> 03:44.856
  SPARED ABSOLUTELY NO EXPENSE.

03:44.858 --> 03:46.625
AS I AM WELL AWARE.

03:46.627 --> 03:48.010
       NOTHING LIKE HAVING

03:48.011 --> 03:49.394
      A FAMILY MEMBER PRIVY
        TO YOUR FINANCES.

03:49.396 --> 03:50.762
NOW, BART, CHRIS
HAS BEEN VERY GOOD

03:50.764 --> 03:52.731
AT BEING THE EXECUTOR
OF YOUR ESTATE.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.500
   OH, IT'S NOT MY ESTATE YET.

03:54.501 --> 03:56.268
   AT LEAST NOT UNTIL WE HEAR
 THE END OF GRANDMOTHER'S WILL.

03:56.270 --> 03:57.369
   WELL, IT WON'T BE LONG NOW.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.054
          NO, IT WON'T.

03:59.055 --> 04:00.738
      LET ME GIVE YOU GUYS
         THE GRAND TOUR.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.307
            THIS WAY.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.410
           OH, MY GOD.

04:05.412 --> 04:06.778
           MALCOLM...

04:06.780 --> 04:08.847
   I'VE OF COURSE INCORPORATED
    THE LATEST TECHNOLOGIES.

04:08.849 --> 04:11.817
         GOT A HOME GYM,
  BIG-SCREEN TVS, DVD PLAYERS,

04:11.819 --> 04:13.752
    AND GOT DIAL-UP INTERNET.

04:16.624 --> 04:18.690
          [CATHY]: WOW!

04:18.692 --> 04:20.392
THIS IS IMPRESSIVE.

04:20.394 --> 04:22.561
I THINK IT'S GOING TO
MAKE A WONDERFUL HOME

04:22.563 --> 04:23.862
FOR A NICE GIRL ONE DAY.

04:23.864 --> 04:25.364
  WELL, I'VE YET TO MEET A GIRL

04:25.366 --> 04:26.598
     WHO COULD HOLD A CANDLE
          TO YOU, MOM.

04:26.600 --> 04:29.401
            COME ON.
    LET ME SHOW YOU THE REST.

04:30.804 --> 04:33.272
              [¶¶¶]

04:35.976 --> 04:37.676
     WHAT'S ALL THIS, BART?

04:39.947 --> 04:41.980
              [¶¶¶]

04:43.350 --> 04:44.750
   WELL, THAT'S WHERE I PRAY.

04:44.752 --> 04:45.917
                        I, UH...

04:45.919 --> 04:48.820
DIDN'T REALIZE YOU WERE
STILL SO RELIGIOUS.

04:48.822 --> 04:49.955
                      [CHUCKLES]
                      WELL...

04:49.957 --> 04:51.390
                   YOU MAY THINK

04:51.392 --> 04:52.791
     IT WAS ALL THOSE YEARS
       OF PSYCHIATRIC CARE

04:52.793 --> 04:54.626
           THAT GOT ME
      TO WHERE I AM TODAY,

04:54.628 --> 04:55.994
 BUT IT WAS BY THE GRACE OF GOD

04:55.996 --> 04:58.430
 THAT I WAS ABLE TO LIFT MYSELF
      FROM MY SORRY STATE.

04:58.432 --> 05:00.866
    MALCOLM WAS A DEVOUT MAN

05:00.868 --> 05:02.567
         AND HE WENT ON
       TO BUILD AN EMPIRE.

05:02.569 --> 05:05.604
    I'M GONNA ACCOMPLISH EVEN
  GREATER THINGS, GOD WILLING.

05:05.606 --> 05:07.572
 I'VE ACTUALLY HAD MY LAST NAME
 LEGALLY CHANGED TO "FOXWORTH,"

05:07.574 --> 05:09.308
 JUST TO KEEP HIS LEGACY ALIVE.

05:09.310 --> 05:11.610
BART! HOW COULD YOU
DO THAT WITHOUT TELLING US?

05:11.612 --> 05:13.879
YOU KNOW MALCOLM
WASN'T A GOOD MAN.

05:15.382 --> 05:16.548
             OH, I KNOW
             ALL OF OUR FAMILY'S

05:16.550 --> 05:18.450
                   DIRTY LITTLE
                   SECRETS, MOM.

05:18.452 --> 05:20.552
                YES-- [CHUCKLES]

05:20.554 --> 05:23.388
              MALCOLM WAS
              A SADISTIC TYRANT,

05:23.390 --> 05:25.590
             BUT YOU MUST ADMIRE
             HIS ACHIEVEMENTS.

05:25.592 --> 05:27.959
      AND, WELL, CHRIS HERE
       MAY HAVE RAISED ME.

05:27.961 --> 05:31.530
       HE IS YOUR BROTHER,
 SO THAT WOULD BE ALL KINDS OF--

05:31.532 --> 05:32.931
          BART, I THINK
        WE'RE ENTITLED TO

05:32.933 --> 05:35.500
    A LITTLE BIT MORE RESPECT
           THAN THAT.

05:36.837 --> 05:38.537
        YOU GUYS PROBABLY
       WANT TO FRESHEN UP.

05:38.539 --> 05:41.039
                 LET ME SHOW YOU
                 TO YOUR ROOM.

05:43.444 --> 05:44.943
            I THOUGHT
    YOU'D BE MOST COMFORTABLE

05:44.945 --> 05:46.879
       IN CORRINE'S WING.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.814
      IT'S ONE OF THE MOST
   LAVISH SUITES IN THE HOUSE.

05:50.117 --> 05:52.484
              [¶¶¶]

05:53.620 --> 05:55.854
         AND, OF COURSE,
       CORRINE'S SWAN BED.

05:55.856 --> 05:56.955
ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

05:56.957 --> 05:58.757
I HIRED
A WORLD-RENOWNED ARTISAN

05:58.759 --> 06:00.859
          TO HAND-CARVE
      A METICULOUS REPLICA.

06:00.861 --> 06:02.794
           I JUST KNEW
    YOU'D APPRECIATE IT, MOM.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.763
    AND ONCE I'VE GET CONTROL
    OF THE FOXWORTH FORTUNE,

06:04.765 --> 06:06.131
          I CAN FINALLY
       FULFILL MY DESTINY.

06:06.133 --> 06:07.599
           NO OFFENSE,

06:07.601 --> 06:09.501
      BUT A DOCTOR DOES NOT
    A FINANCIAL GENIUS MAKE.

06:10.838 --> 06:12.971
        I'LL LET YOU TWO
         GET SETTLED IN.

06:12.973 --> 06:15.407
        JORY AND MELODIE
    WILL BE ARRIVING SHORTLY.

06:17.378 --> 06:18.677
         [SIGHS HEAVILY]

06:18.679 --> 06:20.579
   BE NICE WHEN WE DON'T HAVE
    THIS FINANCIAL SITUATION

06:20.581 --> 06:21.913
BETWEEN US ANYMORE.

06:21.915 --> 06:22.981
           HE'S YOUNG,
   HE WANTS HIS INDEPENDENCE.

06:22.983 --> 06:24.716
    YOU KNOW WHAT HE'S LIKE.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.685
           BUT THIS...
     OBSESSION WITH MALCOLM,

06:26.687 --> 06:27.886
         IT'S TROUBLING.

06:27.888 --> 06:28.987
DON'T DWELL ON IT.

06:31.525 --> 06:32.858
                      OKAY.

06:35.062 --> 06:37.629
      LET'S JUST ENJOY OURSELVES
      WHILE WE'RE HERE.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.766
IN MOTHER'S BED?

06:40.768 --> 06:43.769
THE OLD LADY WOULD
TURN OVER IN HER GRAVE.

06:43.771 --> 06:46.438
                           GOOD.

06:46.440 --> 06:48.807
SOUNDS LIKE
A GOOD IDEA THEN.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.845
              [¶¶¶]

07:05.125 --> 07:07.058
       JORY! YOU MADE IT.

07:07.060 --> 07:08.560
        WELL, IF IT ISN'T
      THE <i> CREME DE LA CREME</i>

07:08.562 --> 07:10.195
     OF THE NEW YORK BALLET.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.463
          [JORY LAUGHS]

07:11.465 --> 07:12.831
        GOOD TO SEE YOU.

07:12.833 --> 07:14.099
                  YOU'RE LOOKING
                  QUITE FIT!

07:14.101 --> 07:16.034
YEAH. HEY, MEL.

07:16.036 --> 07:17.035
               HI.

07:19.506 --> 07:21.573
OH, AND THANK YOU,
GUYS, AGAIN SO MUCH,

07:21.575 --> 07:23.208
FOR AGREEING TO DANCE
AT MY CELEBRATION.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.477
IT IS ABSOLUTELY
GONNA MAKE THE NIGHT,

07:25.479 --> 07:27.095
HAVING A SPECIAL
PERFORMANCE

07:27.096 --> 07:28.712
BY MY FAMOUS BROTHER
AND SISTER-IN-LAW.

07:28.715 --> 07:30.048
         ACTUALLY, BART,

07:30.050 --> 07:32.184
     I'M SORRY, BUT WE CAN'T
     PERFORM AT YOUR PARTY.

07:32.186 --> 07:33.919
YOU KNOW HOW IMPORTANT
THIS NIGHT IS TO ME.

07:33.921 --> 07:36.054
        MEL'S BEEN HAVING
       SOME COMPLICATIONS

07:36.056 --> 07:38.924
             AND HER DOCTOR JUST
             TOLD US SHE CAN'T.

07:38.926 --> 07:40.091
        WHAT DO YOU MEAN
       BY "COMPLICATIONS"?

07:41.695 --> 07:43.462
           WELL, UM...

07:43.464 --> 07:47.132
        WE WANTED TO WAIT
 UNTIL EVERYONE WAS HERE, BUT...

07:47.134 --> 07:48.600
          I'M PREGNANT.

07:48.602 --> 07:49.734
             TWINS.

07:49.736 --> 07:51.603
TWINS?
OH, MY GOODNESS!

07:51.605 --> 07:52.771
            OH! CONGRATULATIONS!

07:52.773 --> 07:53.872
OH, HONEY,
CONGRATULATIONS!

07:53.874 --> 07:55.607
HOW FAR ALONG
ARE YOU?

07:55.609 --> 07:57.008
                ALMOST 19 WEEKS.

07:57.010 --> 07:58.043
   I'M GOING TO BE A GRANDMA!

07:58.045 --> 07:59.010
            [CHRIS]:
    CONGRATULATIONS, DARLING.

07:59.012 --> 08:00.512
  BUT YOU'RE NOT EVEN SHOWING.

08:02.115 --> 08:03.949
                     WE HAD SUCH

08:03.951 --> 08:06.117
A DIFFICULT TIME
GETTING PREGNANT.

08:06.119 --> 08:07.552
               WE CAN'T RISK IT.

08:07.554 --> 08:09.120
                      I'M SORRY.

08:09.122 --> 08:11.823
    I UNDERSTAND.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.692
                  I'M HAPPY
                  TO DANCE SOLO.

08:13.694 --> 08:16.127
HEY. THAT
WOULD BE GREAT.

08:16.129 --> 08:18.129
YOU KNOW, PREGNANCY
REALLY BECOMES YOU, MEL.

08:19.967 --> 08:21.500
                      THANK YOU.

08:21.502 --> 08:22.934
       ¶ DON'T BE A FOOL ¶

08:22.936 --> 08:27.806
       ¶ 'CAUSE I'M STILL
        NOT OVER YOU... ¶

08:27.808 --> 08:29.491
     NINE YEARS OF MARRIAGE,

08:29.492 --> 08:31.175
  AND THEY'RE STILL GOING AT IT
       LIKE DOGS IN HEAT.

08:31.178 --> 08:33.111
                    WELL, THAT'S
                    WHAT HAPPENS

08:33.113 --> 08:36.815
           WHEN YOU'RE PARTNERS
           IN LIFE AND IN DANCE.

08:38.552 --> 08:40.751
   JORY'S FATHER WAS VOLATILE,

08:40.754 --> 08:42.953
         BUT HE WAS ALSO
        QUITE PASSIONATE.

08:42.956 --> 08:45.624
"GO, TAKE TO YOURSELF
A WIFE OF HARLOTRY

08:45.626 --> 08:47.526
AND HAVE CHILDREN
OF HARLOTRY."

08:47.528 --> 08:49.761
         WELL, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
         <i> THE BIBLE</i> SAYS, BART,

08:49.763 --> 08:51.296
                BUT I DO KNOW
                THAT SEX BETWEEN

08:51.298 --> 08:53.265
                 TWO PEOPLE WHO
                 LOVE EACH OTHER

08:53.267 --> 08:55.667
              IS A GOOD
              AND NATURAL THING.

08:57.738 --> 08:59.571
             DON'T YOU EVER WANT
             TO BE IN LOVE?

08:59.573 --> 09:00.972
          [BART SIGHS]

09:00.974 --> 09:02.641
          I DON'T KNOW.

09:02.643 --> 09:04.643
            IT'S HARD
   NOT TO FEEL BITTER ABOUT IT

09:04.645 --> 09:06.878
  WHEN YOU CONSIDER MY ORIGIN.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.180
           YOU SEDUCED
    MY GRANDMOTHER'S HUSBAND

09:09.182 --> 09:10.248
       TO GET BACK AT HER,

09:10.250 --> 09:12.250
      AND I WAS THE RESULT.

09:12.252 --> 09:15.620
   NOT THE MOST AUSPICIOUS WAY
     TO COME INTO THE WORLD.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.690
                  NO, IT WASN'T.

09:21.228 --> 09:23.695
             AND I'LL BE FOREVER
             SORRY ABOUT THAT.

09:24.765 --> 09:26.932
                   BUT NOT ABOUT
                   HAVING YOU.

09:28.068 --> 09:30.702
             AND I KNOW THERE IS
             A WOMAN OUT THERE,

09:30.704 --> 09:33.171
           JUST WAITING TO SPEND
           HER LIFE WITH YOU.

09:35.676 --> 09:38.743
              [¶¶¶]

09:43.817 --> 09:48.687
    ¶ YOU KNOW YOU'RE A VIXEN
     YOU KNOW YOU'RE A FOX ¶

09:48.689 --> 09:52.357
          ¶ A FOXY LADY
     WHO NEVER GETS CAUGHT ¶

09:52.359 --> 09:55.760
 ¶ YOU JUST LEAD THEM AROUND ¶¶

10:00.734 --> 10:02.067
   OKAY. THIS PLACE IS BEYOND.

10:02.069 --> 10:03.301
                    OH, CINDY!
                    HOW ARE YOU?

10:03.303 --> 10:04.669
YOU MADE ME THINK

10:04.671 --> 10:06.271
THAT THIS PLACE WAS
JUST AS SAD AND CREEPY

10:06.273 --> 10:07.672
AS IT WAS WHEN
YOU WERE A GIRL!

10:07.674 --> 10:08.773
THAT IS SO NOT TRUE!

10:08.775 --> 10:10.041
            YEAH, BART'S DONE
            A LOT TO WARM IT UP.

10:10.043 --> 10:11.176
        -THERE'S MY GIRL!
           -HI, DADDY.

10:11.178 --> 10:12.978
        -[CHRIS]: OH! HI!
          -[SMOOCHING]

10:14.615 --> 10:16.147
              -YES!
           -HEY, BOYS!

10:16.149 --> 10:17.983
LOOK WHO'S HERE!

10:17.985 --> 10:20.085
[CINDY]: WOW.

10:20.087 --> 10:21.820
        WHEN DID BART GET
         SO EFFING HOT?

10:21.822 --> 10:23.355
           [CHUCKLES]

10:23.357 --> 10:25.724
          HE USED TO BE
   SUCH AN UGLY LITTLE CRETIN.

10:25.726 --> 10:26.925
        SWEETIE, PLEASE DON'T
        START WITH YOUR BROTHER.

10:26.927 --> 10:29.327
             UM, HI?
        I COME IN PEACE.

10:29.329 --> 10:31.863
   AND HE'S ALWAYS THE ONE WHO
  ALWAYS PROVOKES ME, REMEMBER?

10:31.865 --> 10:32.897
              MM-HMM. WELL,
              I LOVE YOUR DRESS.

10:32.899 --> 10:34.065
           WHERE DID YOU GET IT?

10:34.067 --> 10:35.200
           THANK YOU!
      I GOT IT FROM MILAN.

10:35.202 --> 10:36.768
               [CHRIS]: TELL ME,
               HOW WAS MILAN?

10:36.770 --> 10:37.836
            WELCOME.

10:37.838 --> 10:39.337
TO MY HUMBLE ABODE.

10:39.339 --> 10:41.773
            OH, BART!
    IT IS SO GOOD TO SEE YOU!

10:41.775 --> 10:43.341
               OH!

10:43.343 --> 10:44.709
NICE JOB
DISTRACTING ME

10:44.711 --> 10:46.244
IN THAT TRASHY
LITTLE DRESS.

10:46.246 --> 10:48.947
           EXCUSE ME?
       THIS IS FROM MILAN.

10:48.949 --> 10:51.650
YOU CAN DOLL YOURSELF
UP ALL YOU WANT.

10:51.652 --> 10:52.951
IT DOESN'T
GIVE YOU CLASS.

10:52.953 --> 10:54.019
                  [CHRIS]: BART!

10:54.021 --> 10:55.720
                 APOLOGIZE
                 TO YOUR SISTER.

10:55.722 --> 10:56.888
         WELL, SHE'S NOT
        REALLY MY SISTER.

10:56.890 --> 10:58.156
              DAD.

10:58.158 --> 11:00.025
      BART, WE'RE ALL HERE
     TO CELEBRATE WITH YOU.

11:00.027 --> 11:01.193
                 LET'S NOT START
                 THE WEEKEND--

11:01.194 --> 11:02.360
          I DON'T THINK
     YOU'RE IN ANY POSITION

11:02.362 --> 11:03.828
     TO MAKE DEMANDS, CHRIS.

11:03.830 --> 11:04.929
THIS IS MY HOUSE,

11:04.931 --> 11:06.064
AND AT MY HOUSE,

11:06.066 --> 11:07.232
        I MAKE THE RULES.

11:07.234 --> 11:08.400
        AND I AM YOUR F--

11:08.402 --> 11:09.834
              WHAT?

11:09.836 --> 11:11.403
         YOU'RE MY WHAT?

11:11.405 --> 11:13.705
                 I'M THE MAN
                 WHO RAISED YOU.

11:16.076 --> 11:18.710
     AND I'M THE MAN WHO CAN
   DESTROY YOU WITH ONE WORD.

11:20.213 --> 11:22.080
    I MEAN, COULD YOU IMAGINE

11:22.082 --> 11:24.249
       IF PEOPLE FOUND OUT
       YOUR LITTLE SECRET?

11:24.251 --> 11:25.350
    WHAT IS HE TALKING ABOUT?

11:25.352 --> 11:26.384
               NOTHING, SWEETIE.

11:26.386 --> 11:28.103
                 YOU KNOW, BART,

11:28.104 --> 11:29.821
            YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE
            IF IT WASN'T FOR ME.

11:29.823 --> 11:31.723
      I'VE SAVED YOUR LIFE
   ON MORE THAN ONE OCCASION,

11:31.725 --> 11:33.925
     SOMEDAY, YOU MIGHT WANT
       TO THANK ME FOR IT.

11:33.927 --> 11:35.827
       WELL, THANK YOU...

11:35.829 --> 11:38.396
         "UNCLE CHRIS."

11:43.804 --> 11:45.203
                     [CINDY: HI!

11:45.205 --> 11:46.471
HI.

11:46.473 --> 11:49.007
             AND MELODIE HAS
             SOME EXCITING NEWS.

11:49.009 --> 11:50.442
         HI! WHAT IS IT?

11:50.444 --> 11:53.044
THIS BUNHEAD HAS
TWO BUNS IN THE OVEN.

11:53.046 --> 11:56.314
          OH, MY GOSH!
  ARE YOU-- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!

11:56.316 --> 11:58.316
    TWINS? IF THEY'RE GIRLS,
       I'M GONNA BUY THEM

11:58.318 --> 11:59.851
        THE CUTEST LITTLE
      KIDDIE COUTURE EVER.

11:59.853 --> 12:01.753
     [BART]: I JUST WANT TO
   APOLOGIZE FOR MY OUTBURST.

12:01.755 --> 12:02.987
      ALL THE PREPARATIONS

12:02.989 --> 12:05.256
         FOR THIS PARTY
  HAVE ME A LITTLE BIT ON EDGE.

12:05.258 --> 12:07.192
                     WELL, BART,
                     THAT IS...

12:07.194 --> 12:09.360
                    THAT'S QUITE
                    ALL RIGHT.

12:09.362 --> 12:10.795
SO TELL US ABOUT

12:10.797 --> 12:12.430
   THIS BIRTHDAY SPECTACULAR.

12:12.432 --> 12:16.301
  WELL, IT WAS GONNA BE UNLIKE
 ANYTHING YOU'D EVER SEEN, BUT--

12:16.303 --> 12:17.902
BUT WE SPOILED IT.

12:17.904 --> 12:21.372
     BART, I REALLY DO WISH
 I COULD DANCE DELILAH FOR YOU.

12:21.374 --> 12:22.841
UH, I--

12:22.843 --> 12:24.242
      I CAN DANCE DELILAH.
            I MEAN--

12:24.244 --> 12:26.228
  I MIGHT NOT BE A PROFESSIONAL
            LIKE MEL,

12:26.229 --> 12:28.213
         BUT I-I'VE BEEN
 TAKING DANCE CLASSES EVERY DAY.

12:28.215 --> 12:29.314
             PLEASE?

12:29.316 --> 12:30.882
      PLEASE, JORY? PLEASE?

12:30.884 --> 12:32.517
  I PROMISE-- MEL CAN TEACH ME
        THE DANCE MOVES,

12:32.519 --> 12:36.054
          AND I PROMISE
      I'LL MAKE YOU PROUD.

12:36.056 --> 12:37.355
         IF JORY THINKS
        YOU'RE UP TO IT.

12:37.357 --> 12:40.125
I'M NOT GONNA
TAKE IT EASY ON YOU.

12:40.127 --> 12:41.793
                 I WON'T
                 DISAPPOINT YOU.

12:41.795 --> 12:43.461
     AND IF YOU EMBARRASS ME
     IN FRONT OF MY GUESTS,

12:43.463 --> 12:45.797
  IT'S YOUR HEAD ON A PLATTER.

12:50.003 --> 12:52.771
  [BART]: WOULD YOU CONNECT ME
         TO AN ADJUSTER?

12:52.773 --> 12:54.305
  YEAH, I'M HAVING A HUGE EVENT
          AT MY HOUSE,

12:54.307 --> 12:56.508
 AND I WAS WONDERING IF I SHOULD
     UP MY INSURANCE POLICY.

12:56.510 --> 12:59.878
         AND THAT COVERS
       ILLNESS AND INJURY?

12:59.880 --> 13:01.913
             GREAT.

13:01.915 --> 13:04.249
              [¶¶¶]

13:25.238 --> 13:26.871
         HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

13:26.873 --> 13:28.807
        -HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
        -HELLO, CHILDREN.

13:28.809 --> 13:31.342
WOW, MOM,
YOU LOOK STUNNING.

13:31.344 --> 13:32.544
THANK YOU, SWEETIE.

13:32.546 --> 13:33.978
AND YOU'VE NEVER
LOOKED MORE HANDSOME.

13:33.980 --> 13:35.880
         [CINDY]: AHEM.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.984
              [¶¶¶]

14:00.240 --> 14:03.041
              [¶¶¶]

14:03.043 --> 14:05.009
            [CATHY]:
         CINDY, SWEETIE.

14:05.011 --> 14:06.477
COULD YOU PLEASE
GO AND PUT ON

14:06.479 --> 14:08.279
THAT BLUE DRESS
THAT I LAID OUT FOR YOU?

14:08.281 --> 14:10.281
  MOM, IF YOU WOULD READ <i> VOGUE,</i>

14:10.283 --> 14:12.150
      YOU'D KNOW THIS DRESS
       IS VERY <i> AU COURANT.</i>

14:12.152 --> 14:13.852
                 [CHRIS]: PLEASE
                 GO CHANGE?

14:13.854 --> 14:15.286
                LET'S NOT HAVE
                A SCENE TONIGHT.

14:15.288 --> 14:17.989
     I THINK I'M OLD ENOUGH
 TO CHOOSE WHAT I WANT TO WEAR.

14:17.991 --> 14:20.391
      BESIDES, I'M WEARING
     BART'S FAVORITE COLOR.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.394
I KNOW YOU DON'T
ALWAYS EXERCISE

14:23.396 --> 14:24.495
THE BEST JUDGEMENT,

14:24.497 --> 14:25.964
BEING ADOPTED AND ALL,

14:25.966 --> 14:27.332
BUT I CAN'T HAVE YOU
DRESS LIKE THAT

14:27.334 --> 14:28.600
IN FRONT OF MY GUESTS.

14:28.602 --> 14:29.968
         YOU ALWAYS SAY
       I LOOK LIKE A SLUT,

14:29.970 --> 14:31.369
            I THOUGHT
 I MIGHT AS WELL DRESS LIKE ONE.

14:31.371 --> 14:33.504
OKAY, THAT'S ENOUGH.

14:33.506 --> 14:35.907
YOU'VE HAD YOUR FUN.
TIME TO CHANGE.

14:37.143 --> 14:40.078
                 DON'T EVER
                 TOUCH ME AGAIN.

14:45.118 --> 14:47.619
         [PARTY BUSTLING
     WITH CHATTER AND MUSIC]

14:47.621 --> 14:49.454
YO! CAMBRIDGE
IN THE HOUSE!

14:49.456 --> 14:51.356
          -HEY, BUDDY!
        -WHAT'S UP, MAN?

14:51.358 --> 14:52.924
         -BIRTHDAY BOY!
        -GOOD TO SEE YOU!

14:52.926 --> 14:54.158
-YOU DON'T LOOK THAT MUCH OLDER.
     -AW, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

14:54.160 --> 14:56.394
HEY, JORY, COME HERE.

14:56.396 --> 14:59.430
KEVIN, THIS IS THE MAN,
MY BROTHER, JORY MARQUET,

14:59.432 --> 15:02.000
AND HIS WONDERFUL WIFE
AND PARTNER, MELODIE.

15:02.002 --> 15:03.434
        WHAT A PRIVILEGE.

15:03.436 --> 15:04.969
    WE'VE ALL BEEN FOLLOWING
          YOUR CAREERS

15:04.971 --> 15:06.471
      SINCE THE EARLY DAYS
          IN NEW YORK.

15:06.473 --> 15:08.306
         WE'RE BIG FANS.

15:08.308 --> 15:09.908
    -HOW KIND OF YOU TO SAY.
           -THANK YOU.

15:09.910 --> 15:11.042
             -HERE.
         -OH, EXCELLENT.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.111
         -ON THE HOUSE!
            -CHEERS.

15:15.548 --> 15:19.484
             WOW! NOW, THAT IS
             A HUGE IMPROVEMENT.

15:19.486 --> 15:21.586
IF BY "IMPROVEMENT,"
YOU MEAN "HIDEOUS,"

15:21.588 --> 15:23.488
     THEN YEAH.

15:23.490 --> 15:25.924
ARE YOU GONNA
MAKE HIM APOLOGIZE?

15:25.926 --> 15:27.959
   SWEETIE, YOU DO KNOW YOU GO
 OUT OF YOUR WAY TO PROVOKE HIM.

15:27.961 --> 15:29.327
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

15:29.329 --> 15:30.628
IT'S LIKE
SOMETHING ABOUT HIM

15:30.630 --> 15:32.497
MAKES ME WANT TO GET
A RISE OUT OF HIM.

15:32.499 --> 15:34.365
    WHATEVER.

15:34.367 --> 15:36.234
IF ANYTHING,
MY HATE FOR HIM

15:36.236 --> 15:37.602
WILL HELP FUEL
MY DANCING FOR TONIGHT.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.571
          EXACTLY. CHANNEL IT
          INTO YOUR PERFORMANCE.

15:40.573 --> 15:43.107
              [¶¶¶]

15:46.246 --> 15:47.712
         WELL, YOU KNOW

15:47.714 --> 15:50.048
    SHE'S CORRINE FOXWORTH'S
            DAUGHTER,

15:50.050 --> 15:51.349
        THE ONE WHO CAME
     TO THAT CHRISTMAS PARTY

15:51.351 --> 15:53.384
    AND MADE THAT BIG SCENE.

15:55.088 --> 15:57.021
              [¶¶¶]

15:57.023 --> 15:58.656
SO DO YOU
COME HERE OFTEN?

15:58.658 --> 16:00.992
               HEY, SWEETIE.

16:00.994 --> 16:03.161
                 YOU KNOW, UM...

16:03.163 --> 16:05.229
               YOU HAVE REALLY
               OUTDONE YOURSELF.

16:05.231 --> 16:08.366
           I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.

16:08.368 --> 16:10.468
      THANKS.

16:12.339 --> 16:14.205
           YOU KNOW,
           I REMEMBER THE MOMENT

16:14.207 --> 16:15.506
               THE NURSE PUT YOU
               IN MY ARMS.

16:15.508 --> 16:17.342
        YOU WERE CRYING SO HARD,

16:17.344 --> 16:20.645
      AND YOUR LITTLE HANDS WERE
      BALLED UP INTO FISTS.

16:20.647 --> 16:22.680
           THE MINUTE YOU LOOKED
           UP INTO MY EYES,

16:22.682 --> 16:25.316
               THIS SMILE CREPT
               ACROSS YOUR FACE.

16:25.318 --> 16:26.584
                 AND YOU HAVEN'T
                 ALWAYS BEEN

16:26.586 --> 16:28.753
               THAT GENEROUS
               WITH YOUR SMILES.

16:30.023 --> 16:32.590
I'M SURE JORY
WAS ALL SMILES.

16:32.592 --> 16:35.660
        WELL, YOU EACH HAD
        A DIFFERENT PERSONALITY.

16:35.662 --> 16:38.563
         BUT YOU WANTED ME
         WITH YOU NIGHT AND DAY.

16:38.565 --> 16:40.765
              I'D TRY TO PUT YOU
              IN YOUR CRIB,

16:40.767 --> 16:43.368
                   AND YOU WOULD
                   JUST SCREAM.

16:43.370 --> 16:44.736
       SO I WAS DEMANDING
           EVEN THEN?

16:44.738 --> 16:46.070
                          HEY...

16:46.072 --> 16:48.373
        I LOVED YOU FROM
    THE MOMENT YOU WERE BORN,

16:48.375 --> 16:50.641
                   JUST LIKE
                   YOUR BROTHER.

16:54.781 --> 16:57.048
                  SWEETIE--

16:57.049 --> 16:59.316
     WOULD YOU MIND GETTING ME
     ANOTHER GLASS OF CHAMPAGNE?

16:59.319 --> 17:01.052
         OF COURSE NOT.

17:01.054 --> 17:02.320
                      THANK YOU.

17:05.290 --> 17:08.291
              [¶¶¶]

17:13.032 --> 17:16.233
      I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE
  WE GOT TO MEET JORY MARQUET.

17:16.236 --> 17:18.469
       MY MOM'S GONNA DIE
        WHEN I TELL HER.

17:21.674 --> 17:24.509
             TIME TO GET
             THIS PARTY STARTED.

17:27.547 --> 17:30.314
        [APPLAUSE RISES]

17:33.386 --> 17:34.652
      THANK YOU ALL SO MUCH

17:34.654 --> 17:37.455
     FOR COMING TO CELEBRATE
        MY 25th BIRTHDAY.

17:37.457 --> 17:40.091
 BUT, FOR THE NEXT FEW MOMENTS,
       IT'S NOT ABOUT ME.

17:40.093 --> 17:41.826
        IT IS MY PLEASURE

17:41.828 --> 17:44.495
           TO PRESENT
      "SAMSON AND DELILAH,"

17:44.497 --> 17:46.597
      DANCED BY MY BROTHER,
          JORY MARQUET,

17:46.599 --> 17:49.634
          AND-- MAKING
     HER DEBUT PERFORMANCE--

17:49.636 --> 17:51.202
   OUR ADOPTED SISTER, CINDY.

17:51.204 --> 17:52.837
             ENJOY.

17:52.839 --> 17:55.773
          [APPLAUDING]

18:05.218 --> 18:08.553
              [¶¶¶]

18:25.805 --> 18:27.672
                     SHE'S DOING
                     SO WELL.

18:27.674 --> 18:29.240
  MOST CERTAINLY.

18:29.242 --> 18:31.275
              [¶¶¶]

18:52.232 --> 18:55.133
          YOU WOULD HAVE MADE
          A MUCH BETTER DELILAH.

18:58.638 --> 19:01.639
              [¶¶¶]

19:16.923 --> 19:19.557
          [JORY GROANS]

19:19.559 --> 19:22.260
        [APPLAUSE RISES]

19:26.366 --> 19:27.565
HE'S NOT GETTING UP.

19:27.567 --> 19:29.333
                        MELODIE.

19:31.204 --> 19:32.637
      [APPLAUSE TAPERS OFF]

19:32.639 --> 19:34.405
        [CINDY SHRIEKS]:
       GET IT OFF OF HIM!

19:34.407 --> 19:35.640
                           JORY!

19:35.642 --> 19:36.807
         -[JORY GROANS]
  -SOMEONE TURN UP THE LIGHTS!

19:36.809 --> 19:39.710
              SON!

19:39.712 --> 19:41.212
                         NO. NO!

19:41.214 --> 19:42.647
            IT WASN'T
     SUPPOSED TO FALL DOWN!

19:42.649 --> 19:44.549
         THE BEAM WASN'T
     SUPPOSED TO COME DOWN!

19:44.551 --> 19:45.716
NO! IT'S CRUSHING HIM.

19:45.718 --> 19:47.685
        BART! CALL 9-1-1!

19:47.687 --> 19:49.220
OH, MY GOD! HELP HIM!
DO SOMETHING!

19:49.222 --> 19:51.389
JORY, PLEASE DON'T DIE!

19:51.391 --> 19:53.357
DON'T DIE,
PLEASE!

20:02.202 --> 20:04.802
        IT WAS A MISTAKE
      GOING TO THAT HOUSE!

20:04.804 --> 20:07.838
 THE WORST MISTAKE OF OUR LIVES,
      AND NOW HE'S PAYING,

20:07.840 --> 20:09.674
    AND HE'S GONNA DIE YOUNG,

20:09.676 --> 20:11.576
          LIKE HIS DAD,
           I KNOW IT.

20:11.578 --> 20:13.844
       YOU'RE JUST EXHAUSTED.
       OKAY? YOU NEED SOME REST.

20:13.846 --> 20:15.346
I'LL PUT HER
IN A CAB.

20:15.348 --> 20:16.847
      I CAN TAKE HER BACK.

20:16.849 --> 20:19.450
      [WEEPING]

20:21.688 --> 20:23.254
             NO. NO!

20:23.256 --> 20:24.522
PLEASE, NO!

20:24.524 --> 20:25.823
           -IT'S OKAY.
              -NO!

20:28.661 --> 20:30.761
              [¶¶¶]

20:49.349 --> 20:51.682
              [¶¶¶]

20:57.857 --> 21:00.992
            [SOBBING]

21:00.994 --> 21:02.960
                     OH, JORY...

21:07.000 --> 21:08.866
            [EXHALES]

21:10.837 --> 21:13.337
              MOM?

21:13.339 --> 21:15.806
                        SWEETIE.

21:15.808 --> 21:18.442
                    HOW ARE
                    YOU FEELING?

21:20.013 --> 21:22.813
      I FEEL OKAY, I GUESS.

21:26.352 --> 21:27.652
            [GRUNTS]

21:28.988 --> 21:31.656
             DAD...

21:31.658 --> 21:33.524
      I CAN'T MOVE MY LEGS.

21:33.526 --> 21:35.926
     I-I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS!

21:39.866 --> 21:43.634
  I'LL BE HONEST WITH YOU, SON.

21:46.773 --> 21:48.773
        I'M... PARALYZED.

21:48.775 --> 21:50.308
            AREN'T I?

21:51.444 --> 21:53.511
        YOUR SPINAL CORD
          WAS SEVERED.

21:55.315 --> 21:56.547
              SO...

21:56.549 --> 21:58.916
  I'M NEVER GONNA DANCE AGAIN,

21:58.918 --> 22:00.484
              AM I?

22:00.486 --> 22:01.919
       I'M SO SORRY, JORY.

22:01.921 --> 22:04.522
[JORY GASPS AND SOBS]

22:07.994 --> 22:11.495
       [SOBBING CONTINUES]

22:24.010 --> 22:25.976
  OKAY, MELODIE, THAT'S ENOUGH.

22:25.978 --> 22:27.678
     GET UP. YOU'RE VISITING
       YOUR HUSBAND TODAY.

22:27.680 --> 22:28.946
     GET UP!

22:28.948 --> 22:30.614
      LET ME GO. LET ME GO!
     YOU'LL HURT THE BABIES!

22:30.616 --> 22:32.516
              YOU KNOW I HAVEN'T
              BEEN ABLE TO

22:32.518 --> 22:34.385
             LEAVE THIS ROOM
             SINCE THE ACCIDENT.

22:36.556 --> 22:37.755
DO YOU REALLY THINK

22:37.757 --> 22:39.790
YOU'RE THE FIRST WIFE
TO SUFFER A TRAGEDY?

22:39.792 --> 22:41.692
I WAS EXPECTING JORY

22:41.694 --> 22:44.762
WHEN HIS FATHER WAS
KILLED IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

22:44.764 --> 22:47.398
YOU SHOULD BE GRATEFUL
HE'S STILL ALIVE.

22:47.400 --> 22:48.632
           [SNIFFLING]

22:48.634 --> 22:49.967
   I CAN'T SEE HIM LIKE THAT.

22:49.969 --> 22:51.669
            I CAN'T.

22:55.742 --> 22:58.576
   JORY JUST NEEDS TO KNOW...

22:59.779 --> 23:01.712
 THAT YOU STILL CARE ABOUT HIM.

23:01.714 --> 23:04.482
SO YOU NEED TO
SUMMON UP SOME COURAGE,

23:04.484 --> 23:07.385
AND GO BE A WIFE
TO YOUR HUSBAND.

23:08.921 --> 23:12.623
         HOW CAN WE LIVE
   IF WE CAN'T DANCE TOGETHER?

23:12.625 --> 23:15.926
           WHY DID THIS
           HAVE TO HAPPEN TO US?

23:15.928 --> 23:17.027
                         WHY?

23:17.029 --> 23:19.063
  WHY DID THIS HAVE TO HAPPEN?

23:19.065 --> 23:22.066
       SWEETIE, COME HERE.
           COME HERE.

23:24.971 --> 23:26.771
YOU KNOW, I JUST--
I FIND IT ODD

23:26.773 --> 23:28.939
THAT JORY'S THE ONE
WHO'S NEVER GONNA WALK AGAIN,

23:28.941 --> 23:31.942
BUT MELODIE'S ACTING
LIKE HER LIFE IS OVER.

23:31.944 --> 23:34.478
           WELL, DEPRESSION CAN
           BE VERY DEBILITATING.

23:34.480 --> 23:35.746
           I JUST WISH SHE COULD

23:35.748 --> 23:37.581
               FIND THE STRENGTH
               FOR JORY, THOUGH.

23:37.583 --> 23:39.717
            HE REALLY NEEDS HER.

23:39.719 --> 23:41.519
DAD, CAN I
TELL YOU SOMETHING?

23:41.521 --> 23:43.988
I MEAN, IT MIGHT NOT HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH ANYTHING--

23:43.990 --> 23:45.589
     NO. WHAT IS IT, SWEETHEART?

23:45.591 --> 23:47.258
         WELL, THE NIGHT
        BEFORE THE PARTY,

23:47.259 --> 23:48.926
      I HEARD BART TALKING
          ON THE PHONE

23:48.927 --> 23:50.594
   ABOUT UPPING HIS INSURANCE,
  IN CASE THERE WAS AN INJURY.

23:51.731 --> 23:52.897
        [CHRIS]: THERE'S NO NEED
        TO GET DEFENSIVE, BART.

23:52.899 --> 23:54.165
          WE'RE NOT BLAMING YOU.

23:54.167 --> 23:55.199
       OF COURSE YOU ARE!

23:55.201 --> 23:56.667
  JUST LIKE WHEN WE WERE KIDS,

23:56.669 --> 23:58.569
     AND JORY'S DOG, CLOVER,
           WAS KILLED

23:58.571 --> 23:59.603
AND YOU THOUGHT
I MURDERED HER.

23:59.605 --> 24:00.905
               NO, WE-- WE NEVER
               THOUGHT THAT.

24:00.907 --> 24:02.907
      I MEAN, I WAS THE ONE
     WHO ASKED HIM TO DANCE!

24:02.908 --> 24:04.908
   DON'T YOU THINK THAT I FEEL
   RESPONSIBLE ENOUGH ALREADY?

24:04.911 --> 24:06.944
    MAYBE AN UNINVITED GUEST
       GOT INTO THE PARTY.

24:06.946 --> 24:08.479
     A RIVAL DANCER PERHAPS?

24:08.481 --> 24:10.681
    YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE, KNOW
  HOW CUTTHROAT BALLET CAN BE.

24:10.683 --> 24:12.983
                    YEAH, MAYBE.

24:15.221 --> 24:16.987
         [CHRIS EXHALES]

24:16.989 --> 24:19.957
     YEAH. THAT'S CERTAINLY
         A POSSIBILITY.

24:31.070 --> 24:32.636
    IS THIS HAPPENING AGAIN?

24:33.773 --> 24:35.105
              LIKE WHEN HE TRIED
              TO DROWN CINDY,

24:35.107 --> 24:37.141
                  WHEN THEY
                  WERE CHILDREN?

24:37.143 --> 24:39.610
          PLEASE TELL ME THIS
          ISN'T HAPPENING AGAIN.

24:39.612 --> 24:40.945
    NO. NO.

24:40.947 --> 24:42.480
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

24:42.482 --> 24:44.148
       JORY! MY POOR JORY!

24:44.150 --> 24:46.217
          MY POOR JORY.
            [SOBBING]

24:46.219 --> 24:48.552
IT'S OKAY.

24:48.554 --> 24:51.822
            OH, GOD!
          MY POOR BOY.

24:51.824 --> 24:54.024
              [¶¶¶]

24:57.930 --> 24:59.797
HEY...

24:59.799 --> 25:01.899
YOU DIDN'T COME DOWN
FOR LUNCH AGAIN.

25:05.271 --> 25:07.905
HOW YOU DOING?

25:07.907 --> 25:09.039
        I KNOW THIS CAN'T
        BE EASY FOR YOU,

25:09.041 --> 25:09.974
   WITH THE BABIES ON THE WAY.

25:11.143 --> 25:12.843
  YOUR PARENTS CAN'T UNDERSTAND

25:12.845 --> 25:15.513
       WHY I HAVEN'T BEEN
         TO SEE HIM YET.

25:16.649 --> 25:18.549
            I JUST...

25:18.551 --> 25:21.619
 I HAVE THIS FEAR OF HOSPITALS.

25:21.621 --> 25:25.923
            I LOATHE
THOSE GERM-INFESTED PLACES, TOO.

25:27.593 --> 25:29.860
            I KEEP...

25:29.862 --> 25:33.597
  EXPECTING SOMEONE TO WALK IN
           AND TELL ME

25:33.599 --> 25:34.865
   THAT JORY'S TAKEN HIS LIFE.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.267
      NO!

25:36.269 --> 25:38.769
HEY, DON'T SAY THAT.

25:38.771 --> 25:40.905
YOU KNOW MY BROTHER.

25:40.907 --> 25:42.573
      HE'S THE GOLDEN BOY.

25:42.575 --> 25:44.041
            HE ALWAYS
      COMES OUT THE WINNER.

25:46.012 --> 25:49.580
EVERYBODY'S FOCUSED
ON JORY RIGHT NOW, BUT...

25:49.582 --> 25:51.715
HE'D COUNT ON ME
TO TAKE CARE OF YOU.

25:58.958 --> 26:01.759
       [RHYTHMIC BEEPING]

26:04.297 --> 26:06.664
         I'M TOLD I ONLY
     PUT A MOMENTARY DAMPER

26:06.666 --> 26:07.631
   ON THE NIGHT'S FESTIVITIES.

26:07.633 --> 26:08.699
WELL, YOU'RE ALWAYS

26:08.701 --> 26:11.302
      TRYING TO UPSTAGE ME,
           AREN'T YOU?

26:13.239 --> 26:15.205
     [RAIL CREAKS AND THUDS]

26:16.275 --> 26:17.808
            MELODIE,
       SHE SENDS HER LOVE.

26:17.810 --> 26:19.109
              THIS ISN'T EXACTLY

26:19.111 --> 26:21.712
          THE FAIRYTALE
    SHE SIGNED UP FOR, IS IT?

26:23.583 --> 26:25.683
           THE DOCTORS SAY
           THAT I MIGHT NEVER...

26:25.685 --> 26:28.185
   "FUNCTION" SEXUALLY AGAIN.

26:28.187 --> 26:30.120
                  I CAN'T DANCE.

26:30.122 --> 26:32.790
               I CAN'T MAKE LOVE
               TO MY WIFE.

26:32.792 --> 26:34.959
  WHAT THE HELL'S LEFT FOR ME?

26:34.961 --> 26:36.260
HEY, YOU'VE GOT

26:36.262 --> 26:37.728
  A WIFE WHO LOVES YOU SO MUCH,

26:37.730 --> 26:39.997
    IT'S TOO PAINFUL FOR HER
      TO SEE YOU LIKE THIS.

26:39.999 --> 26:42.333
NOW, I'VE NEVER KNOWN
A LOVE LIKE THAT.

26:45.338 --> 26:47.605
        I'VE NEVER REALLY
       KNOWN LOVE AT ALL.

26:48.741 --> 26:50.975
 I'M NOT SURE WHO HAS IT WORSE,
           ME OR YOU.

26:50.977 --> 26:53.344
  MAYBE IF YOU'D STOP TREATING
   WOMEN LIKE SPERM DEPOSITS,

26:53.346 --> 26:55.846
     YOU'D ACTUALLY REALIZE
        YOU HAVE A HEART.

26:55.848 --> 26:58.182
  HEY, IT'S THE WOMEN WHO WANT
     TO BE TREATED THAT WAY.

26:58.184 --> 27:00.884
 ALL RIGHT, MAYBE IT'S SOMETHING
    THAT I BRING OUT IN THEM.

27:00.886 --> 27:06.023
      LOOK, JORY, WHAT YOU
    AND MELODIE HAVE IS RARE.

27:06.025 --> 27:09.259
    YOU WERE SUCH AN EVIL KID
           GROWING UP.

27:09.261 --> 27:12.096
      WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT
YOU'D TURN OUT TO BE A NICE GUY?

27:12.098 --> 27:14.765
       I'M NOT THAT NICE.

27:16.168 --> 27:19.703
         WHAT I'M REALLY
    TRYING TO DO HERE IS, UH,

27:19.705 --> 27:22.306
   FIGURE OUT A WAY TO GET YOU
OUT OF THIS ANTISEPTIC CESSPOOL,

27:22.308 --> 27:23.974
    SO THAT THE WHOLE FAMILY
         CAN BE TOGETHER

27:23.976 --> 27:26.010
         FOR THE READING
       OF CORRINE'S WILL.

27:26.012 --> 27:29.279
    I MEAN, YOU'RE HOLDING UP
   MY INHERITANCE, YA INVALID.

27:29.281 --> 27:31.281
         [JORY CHUCKLES]

27:41.427 --> 27:43.827
        [BOTH CHUCKLING]

27:45.731 --> 27:47.898
              [¶¶¶]

28:10.056 --> 28:11.255
[DOOR OPENS]

28:18.197 --> 28:20.197
      YOU'RE SO GOOD TO ME.

28:21.867 --> 28:23.967
       HERE.

28:23.969 --> 28:27.204
  I REALLY SHOULDN'T BE MIXING
  WINE WITH MY ANTIDEPRESSANTS.

28:27.206 --> 28:29.306
IT WON'T
DO YOU ANY HARM.

28:29.308 --> 28:31.375
         IT'S THE BABIES
       I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

28:33.379 --> 28:36.480
      I SUPPOSE A SMALL SIP
           WON'T HURT.

28:39.351 --> 28:41.852
              [¶¶¶]

28:51.063 --> 28:53.197
    [HE SETS THE GLASS DOWN]

28:53.199 --> 28:55.432
              [¶¶¶]

29:05.211 --> 29:07.745
                [GASPS] CAREFUL!
                THE BABIES.

29:10.182 --> 29:11.448
         THAT'S BETTER.

29:12.485 --> 29:14.485
              [¶¶¶]

29:22.027 --> 29:23.460
      DAD. DAD...

29:23.462 --> 29:25.262
                WHAT IS IT, SON?

29:25.264 --> 29:27.297
      I'M NOT GONNA BE ABLE
       TO PICK UP MY KIDS.

29:27.299 --> 29:28.499
I WON'T BE ABLE
TO TEACH THEM

29:28.501 --> 29:30.033
HOW TO RIDE A BIKE.

29:30.035 --> 29:32.102
       WHAT KIND OF FATHER
        AM I GOING TO BE?

29:32.104 --> 29:33.871
              THERE ARE FAR MORE
              IMPORTANT THINGS

29:33.873 --> 29:35.405
              THAN THAT
              TO BEING A FATHER.

29:39.411 --> 29:42.112
             [BART]:
    THE PRINCE HAS RETURNED.

29:45.451 --> 29:47.384
     OH, MY BABY.

29:47.386 --> 29:49.787
              I'M SORRY I DIDN'T
              COME TO SEE YOU.

29:49.789 --> 29:52.089
                   I WAS SCARED.

29:52.091 --> 29:53.223
              PLEASE FORGIVE ME?

29:53.225 --> 29:54.925
         YOU'RE MY WIFE.

29:54.927 --> 29:57.795
       I THINK I KNOW WHAT
   A FRAGILE CREATURE YOU ARE.

30:00.499 --> 30:03.066
            AHEM. SO.

30:03.068 --> 30:05.102
         CAN I SHOW YOU
   MY "WELCOME HOME" PRESENT?

30:05.104 --> 30:06.503
       I HAD IT INSTALLED

30:06.505 --> 30:08.906
    SO YOU WOULDN'T BE STUCK
       ON THE FIRST FLOOR.

30:08.908 --> 30:10.140
    I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

30:10.142 --> 30:11.375
      WELL, THEN DON'T SAY
        ANYTHING AT ALL.

30:11.377 --> 30:13.277
COME ON. LET'S GET YOU
UP TO YOUR ROOM.

30:20.553 --> 30:21.985
                      ALL RIGHT.

30:21.987 --> 30:23.387
       WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

30:23.389 --> 30:24.555
        [HOIST WHIRRING]

30:26.492 --> 30:27.958
                   PUT YOUR ARMS
                   AROUND ME.

30:27.960 --> 30:29.827
                     COME ON UP.

30:32.231 --> 30:33.597
             PRETTY SOON, YOU'LL
             BE STRONG ENOUGH

30:33.599 --> 30:34.965
               TO GET IN AND OUT
               OF BED YOURSELF.

30:34.967 --> 30:36.200
          WHERE'S MEL?

30:36.202 --> 30:37.901
SHE WAS FEELING
A BIT QUEASY THIS MORNING,

30:37.903 --> 30:39.269
         SO SHE DECIDED

30:39.271 --> 30:41.438
     TO TAKE A NAP IN ONE OF
        THE GUEST ROOMS.

30:41.440 --> 30:42.973
        MORNING SICKNESS.

30:42.975 --> 30:45.175
    [CINDY]: I CAN'T BELIEVE
   SHE'S NOT HERE TO SEE THIS.

30:45.177 --> 30:47.277
     W-- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:47.279 --> 30:48.712
WHOA! HEY!

30:48.713 --> 30:50.146
      -WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
  -HIS SPINE IS STILL FRAGILE!

30:50.149 --> 30:52.549
YOU'VE BEEN SET
FREE, BROTHER!

30:52.551 --> 30:54.251
                  YOU'RE INSANE!

30:54.253 --> 30:56.453
 IT'S MR. FOXWORTH'S WILD RIDE!

30:56.455 --> 30:58.956
              [¶¶¶]

31:08.067 --> 31:11.602
              [¶¶¶]

31:12.905 --> 31:15.038
 "TO BE READ AFTER MY GRANDSON,

31:15.040 --> 31:19.142
      "BARTHOLOMEW WINSLOW
  SCOTT SHEFFIELD'S 25th YEAR.

31:19.144 --> 31:20.911
        "THE ENTIRETY OF

31:20.913 --> 31:22.880
  "THE CORRINE FOXWORTH WINSLOW
              TRUST

31:22.882 --> 31:25.249
      "WILL BE TURNED OVER
         TO MY GRANDSON,

31:25.251 --> 31:27.084
          "BARTHOLOMEW
    WINSLOW SCOTT SHEFFIELD,

31:27.086 --> 31:29.419
         WHEN HE REACHES
         THE AGE OF 35."

31:29.421 --> 31:30.554
    WHAT?

31:30.556 --> 31:32.823
        "UNTIL THAT TIME,

31:32.824 --> 31:35.091
 "HE WILL RECEIVE AN ANNUAL SUM
          OF $500,000,

31:35.094 --> 31:37.027
     "AND MY FIRST-BORN SON,

31:37.029 --> 31:39.663
      "CHRISTOPHER GARLAND
     DOLLANGANGER SHEFFIELD,

31:39.665 --> 31:41.231
  WILL CONTINUE IN HIS POSITION
          AS TRUSTEE."

31:41.233 --> 31:42.366
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON HERE?

31:42.368 --> 31:43.367
        THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

31:43.369 --> 31:44.635
          THERE'S MORE.

31:44.637 --> 31:46.937
      "SHOULD BARTHOLOMEW,
          AT ANY TIME,

31:46.939 --> 31:48.372
     "BE INSTITUTIONALIZED,

31:48.374 --> 31:49.673
   "FULL CONTROL OF THE ESTATE

31:49.675 --> 31:51.108
           WILL REVERT
      BACK TO CHRISTOPHER."

31:51.110 --> 31:53.176
          [BART]: WHAT?

31:53.178 --> 31:54.945
         THIS IS ABSURD!

31:57.683 --> 32:01.118
    I AM NOT ANSWERING TO YOU
      FOR ANOTHER 10 YEARS!

32:01.120 --> 32:03.320
BART, $500,000 A YEAR

32:03.322 --> 32:05.289
IS STILL QUITE
A LOT OF MONEY.

32:05.291 --> 32:07.057
           OF COURSE,
     YOU'RE HAPPY ABOUT IT!

32:07.059 --> 32:08.292
    YOU'RE STILL IN CONTROL!
       YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE.

32:08.294 --> 32:09.993
             THE ONE
    WHO HAS SINNED THE MOST.

32:09.995 --> 32:11.929
                 OKAY, BART,
                 JUST CALM DOWN.

32:11.931 --> 32:13.397
      YOU PLANNED THIS FROM
   THE BEGINNING, DIDN'T YOU?

32:13.399 --> 32:15.265
       JUST BEEN LAUGHING
 BEHIND MY BACK THE WHOLE TIME!

32:15.267 --> 32:18.135
                  I ASSURE YOU,
                  I HAD NO IDEA.

32:18.137 --> 32:20.203
        WHY IS IT SO HARD

32:20.205 --> 32:22.539
   FOR EVERYONE TO UNDERSTAND
      THAT I JUST WANT <i> YOU</i>

32:22.541 --> 32:25.275
         OUT OF MY LIFE?

32:25.277 --> 32:26.443
          [SHATTERING]

32:30.549 --> 32:32.582
YOU THINK
HE'LL BE OKAY?

32:32.584 --> 32:34.451
    I THINK BART'LL BE FINE.

32:34.453 --> 32:36.620
     HE ALWAYS BOUNCES BACK.

32:36.622 --> 32:38.455
               BUT HE WAS RIGHT.

32:38.457 --> 32:40.257
         PREGNANCY ONLY
    MAKES YOU MORE BEAUTIFUL.

32:40.259 --> 32:44.027
  IF YOU THINK A BEACHED WHALE
          IS BEAUTIFUL.

32:44.029 --> 32:45.963
           WELL, I DO.

32:45.965 --> 32:48.199
        [INHALES SHARPLY]

32:48.200 --> 32:50.434
          I GOT THIS MADDENING
          ITCH ON MY RIGHT CALF.

32:52.104 --> 32:54.471
I THOUGHT, UH...

32:54.473 --> 32:58.675
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T
HAVE FEELING DOWN THERE.

32:58.677 --> 33:01.578
       I DON'T, BUT I GET
      THESE PHANTOM PAINS.

33:04.750 --> 33:07.451
           I WONDER IF
    THERE'S SUCH THING AS...

33:07.453 --> 33:09.519
     PHANTOM PLEASURES, TOO.

33:10.522 --> 33:12.189
DO YOU, UH...

33:12.191 --> 33:15.392
DO YOU NEED ME
TO SCRATCH IT, OR--?

33:15.394 --> 33:17.127
      COME LIE NEXT TO ME.

33:18.197 --> 33:20.097
        JORY, I'M SO BIG.

33:20.099 --> 33:21.665
       I WANT TO FEEL YOU
           AGAINST ME.

33:30.776 --> 33:32.743
           -I'M SORRY.
       -IT'S OKAY, HONEY.

33:32.745 --> 33:34.411
      I JUST-- I FEEL SO...

33:34.413 --> 33:36.380
        HONEY, IT'S OKAY.

33:45.190 --> 33:49.259
     I'M JUST... GONNA SLEEP
   IN ONE OF THE GUEST ROOMS.

33:49.261 --> 33:52.129
           MAYBE AFTER
   THESE BABIES ARE DELIVERED

33:52.131 --> 33:53.764
   AND YOU'RE FEELING BETTER.

33:53.766 --> 33:56.400
            I WANT TO BE BACK
            IN NEW YORK BY THEN.

33:56.402 --> 33:59.236
  NOTHING WILL MAKE ME HAPPIER
  THAN TO SEE YOU DANCE AGAIN.

33:59.238 --> 34:02.172
 I'M GLAD TO HEAR YOU SAY THAT.

34:02.174 --> 34:04.574
            I MEAN...

34:04.576 --> 34:07.477
       YOUR FAMILY'S BEEN
          SO WONDERFUL,

34:08.746 --> 34:12.149
            BUT I...

34:12.150 --> 34:13.784
         [VOICE SHAKES]:
     ...I FEEL TRAPPED HERE.

34:13.786 --> 34:15.819
            AT LEAST
     WE'RE TRAPPED TOGETHER.

34:20.793 --> 34:23.159
              [¶¶¶]

34:27.199 --> 34:29.331
LOVE YOU.

34:30.803 --> 34:33.170
              [¶¶¶]

34:39.143 --> 34:41.344
              [¶¶¶]

34:59.364 --> 35:02.132
              [¶¶¶]

35:04.803 --> 35:06.870
                    JORY, HONEY?

35:09.174 --> 35:11.408
I USED TO BE
SOMETHING IMPORTANT.

35:11.410 --> 35:14.478
 I USED TO DANCE "DON QUIXOTE."

35:14.480 --> 35:17.247
       NOW I CAN'T DANCE.

35:17.249 --> 35:19.416
  I CAN'T MAKE LOVE TO MY WIFE.

35:20.586 --> 35:22.285
          I'M NOTHING.

35:22.287 --> 35:24.888
           OH, THAT IS NOT TRUE.

35:26.458 --> 35:28.458
             YOU ARE EVERYTHING.

35:28.460 --> 35:31.394
             TO ME,
        TO YOUR FATHER...

35:31.396 --> 35:33.630
          TO YOUR WIFE.

35:33.632 --> 35:36.133
WHO CAN'T STAND
THE SIGHT OF ME.

35:37.269 --> 35:39.436
NOT THAT I BLAME HER.

35:41.240 --> 35:44.708
WHO WOULD WANT TO BE
WITH A CRIPPLED EUNUCH?

35:52.584 --> 35:55.485
   OH, HEY, HAVE EITHER OF YOU
          SEEN MELODIE?

35:55.487 --> 35:57.487
                      NO, MA'AM.

36:06.632 --> 36:08.265
         [GROANING AND GRUNTING]

36:16.241 --> 36:18.275
          -OH, MY GOD!
        -[MELODIE GASPS]

36:18.277 --> 36:19.676
                       MOTHER...

36:19.678 --> 36:22.546
    HOW KIND OF YOU TO KNOCK.

36:22.548 --> 36:24.648
             [SIGHS]

36:26.752 --> 36:28.451
     HOW COULD YOU DO THIS?

36:28.453 --> 36:32.222
      JORY HAS STOOD BY YOU
       THROUGH EVERYTHING!

36:32.224 --> 36:36.593
    ALL THE WOMEN I'VE KNOWN
  HAVE BEEN LIARS AND SINNERS.

36:36.595 --> 36:38.728
         UNTIL MELODIE.

36:38.730 --> 36:40.830
     SHE'S THE FIRST PERSON
       TO MAKE ME REALIZE

36:40.832 --> 36:42.632
   HOW BEAUTIFUL LOVE CAN BE.

36:42.634 --> 36:44.801
     I MEAN, ISN'T THAT WHAT
       YOU WANTED FOR ME?

36:44.803 --> 36:47.304
     BUT WHY DID YOU HAVE TO
   CHOOSE YOUR BROTHER'S WIFE?

36:47.306 --> 36:48.572
   I GUESS IT WAS GOD'S WILL.

36:48.574 --> 36:50.307
     IT WAS NOT GOD'S WILL!

36:50.309 --> 36:51.775
            YOU CHOSE
     TO BETRAY YOUR BROTHER!

36:51.777 --> 36:54.344
     DON'T YOU PREACH TO ME
         ABOUT BETRAYAL!

36:55.847 --> 36:57.547
   IS THAT MALCOLM'S JOURNAL?

36:58.784 --> 37:00.650
   WHY DO YOU STILL HAVE THAT?

37:00.652 --> 37:02.919
     IT'S MY MOST TREASURED
           POSSESSION.

37:02.921 --> 37:04.754
DID YOU KNOW
THAT HE HAD

37:04.756 --> 37:07.324
AN INFATUATION
WITH HIS MOTHER?

37:07.326 --> 37:08.858
   THAT IS, UNTIL SHE RAN OFF
         WITH HER LOVER

37:08.860 --> 37:10.794
          AND LEFT HIM
   WITH A FATHER HE DESPISED.

37:10.796 --> 37:12.662
MOM, I'M AFRAID

37:12.664 --> 37:14.564
THAT SOME OF MALCOLM'S
MATERNAL HATRED

37:14.566 --> 37:16.533
MAY HAVE
RUBBED OFF ON ME,

37:16.535 --> 37:18.702
       BECAUSE EVERY TIME
        I SEE YOU AND <i> HIM</i>

37:18.704 --> 37:19.836
       GO INTO YOUR ROOM,

37:19.838 --> 37:21.571
         I AM DISGUSTED.

37:21.573 --> 37:23.340
SO DON'T TRY AND
MAKE ME FEEL BAD

37:23.342 --> 37:24.474
ABOUT WHAT I'M DOING,

37:24.476 --> 37:27.978
        WHEN WHAT YOU DO
       IS FAR, FAR WORSE.

37:29.748 --> 37:32.315
            [SOBBING]

37:33.385 --> 37:35.585
              [¶¶¶]

37:38.824 --> 37:40.390
HAVE YOU SEEN MEL?

37:40.392 --> 37:42.759
             SHE SAID SHE WANTED
             TO STAY IN BED.

37:42.761 --> 37:45.895
       HOW ABOUT I ARRANGE
       A ROMANTIC DINNER,

37:45.897 --> 37:47.831
     JUST FOR THE TWO OF YOU
            TONIGHT?

37:47.833 --> 37:49.933
        HOW'S THAT SOUND?

37:49.935 --> 37:52.902
         ¶ WISH I KNEW ¶

37:52.904 --> 37:57.374
      ¶ WHAT I COULD SAY ¶

37:57.376 --> 38:01.511
    ¶ ONLY YOU I COULD LOVE ¶

38:01.513 --> 38:07.350
    ¶ WHY WON'T YOU STAY... ¶

38:07.352 --> 38:08.985
              [¶¶¶]

38:08.987 --> 38:11.354
   [VOICES AND LAUGHTER BELOW]

38:11.356 --> 38:13.490
     [BART]: IT TAKES WEEKS
      TO GET A RESERVATION.

38:21.867 --> 38:26.436
              [¶¶¶]

38:38.884 --> 38:44.421
              [¶¶¶]

39:21.560 --> 39:23.526
I GOT YOU, SON.

39:23.528 --> 39:24.494
         [JORY GASPING]

39:24.496 --> 39:25.995
YOU'RE OKAY.

39:34.506 --> 39:36.139
           [SOBBING]:
       I DID WANT TO DIE.

39:36.141 --> 39:39.008
          WHY WON'T YOU
           LET ME DIE?

39:40.412 --> 39:42.512
              [¶¶¶]

39:45.717 --> 39:50.553
       SO... DINNER AGAIN
         TOMORROW NIGHT?

39:50.555 --> 39:52.055
                        OKAY.

40:07.873 --> 40:10.473
          WELL, LOOK AT
    WHAT THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

40:10.475 --> 40:12.409
      CATHY, YOU SCARED ME.

40:13.512 --> 40:14.511
    WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:14.513 --> 40:15.745
IS JORY ALL RIGHT?

40:15.747 --> 40:16.980
   YOU ASK THAT LIKE YOU CARE.

40:16.982 --> 40:18.748
        OF COURSE I CARE!

40:18.750 --> 40:20.550
          I LOVE JORY.

40:20.552 --> 40:22.118
      I'LL ALWAYS LOVE HIM,
         YOU KNOW THAT.

40:22.120 --> 40:23.553
   YET YOU STILL STOOD HIM UP.

40:23.555 --> 40:25.021
              AND HERE YOU ARE--

40:25.023 --> 40:26.589
               LIPSTICK SMEARED,

40:26.591 --> 40:28.124
                 ALCOHOL
                 ON YOUR BREATH,

40:28.126 --> 40:30.894
      AND THE SMELL OF
      MY OTHER SON ALL OVER YOU.

40:33.899 --> 40:37.100
      YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NOT
   GONNA MAKE ME FEEL GUILTY.

40:37.102 --> 40:39.769
          I'M A DANCER,
      YOU KNOW HOW WE LIVE.

40:39.771 --> 40:42.772
LIVING FOR THE HIGH
OF THE AUDIENCE APPLAUSE,

40:42.774 --> 40:45.642
   AND JUST HOLDING OUR BREATH
   UNTIL WE CAN GET IT AGAIN.

40:45.644 --> 40:48.545
           AND NOW...
    WE'LL NEVER GET IT AGAIN.

40:48.547 --> 40:49.846
    SO YOU GET YOUR HIGH NOW

40:49.848 --> 40:52.715
       BY DOING SOMETHING
      YOU KNOW IS SO WRONG?

40:56.888 --> 40:58.822
YOU HAVE A LOT OF
NERVE JUDGING ME,

40:58.824 --> 41:00.657
WHEN YOU'VE DONE
MUCH WORSE.

41:02.694 --> 41:03.793
[GASPING]

41:03.795 --> 41:07.230
           JORY TRIED TO
           KILL HIMSELF TONIGHT.

41:07.232 --> 41:08.731
                   MY SON!

41:08.733 --> 41:10.567
                TRIED TO KILL
                HIMSELF TONIGHT!

41:10.569 --> 41:12.235
WHAT? NO...

41:12.237 --> 41:13.903
                 I USED TO THINK

41:13.905 --> 41:15.805
             YOU WERE ONE
             OF THOSE RARITIES--

41:16.875 --> 41:19.542
                A WOMAN WHO WAS
                BEAUTIFUL INSIDE

41:19.544 --> 41:21.578
                        AND OUT.

41:22.581 --> 41:25.148
                  BUT YOU ARE...

41:25.150 --> 41:26.749
                      UGLY.

41:27.886 --> 41:29.719
                YOU'RE DONE
                TRYING TO ESCAPE

41:29.721 --> 41:31.087
          YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES.

41:31.089 --> 41:32.956
                 DO YOU HEAR ME?

41:32.958 --> 41:34.924
                    YOU ARE DONE
                    WITH BART.

41:34.926 --> 41:36.793
                YOU ARE GOING TO
                GROW THE HELL UP

41:36.795 --> 41:38.828
           AND START TAKING CARE
           OF THESE BABIES.

41:38.830 --> 41:40.663
          YOU ARE GOING TO START

41:40.665 --> 41:42.198
              LIVING UP TO
              YOUR WEDDING VOWS,

41:42.200 --> 41:43.933
               OR I WILL DESTROY

41:43.935 --> 41:46.703
                   YOUR PATHETIC
                   LITTLE LIFE.

41:51.810 --> 41:54.844
          I HAD NO IDEA
   YOU COULD BE SUCH A BITCH.

41:54.846 --> 41:58.948
         WELL, CLEARLY,
  YOU DON'T KNOW ME THAT WELL.

42:01.887 --> 42:04.287
     [FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

42:16.167 --> 42:20.136
                  I'M SORRY I...

42:20.138 --> 42:22.672
                  I DISAPPEARED.

42:24.209 --> 42:26.676
                 I DIDN'T MEAN
                 TO NEGLECT YOU.

42:26.678 --> 42:28.177
          I WAS JUST... [SNIFFS]

42:28.179 --> 42:29.946
                 CAUGHT UP
                 IN MY OWN CRAP,

42:29.948 --> 42:31.714
               THAT I COMPLETELY
               FORGOT ABOUT YOU

42:31.716 --> 42:33.883
          AND HOW MUCH
          YOU MUST'VE NEEDED ME.

42:33.885 --> 42:37.754
           AND I WAS SO SELFISH.

42:37.756 --> 42:40.156
          I LOST ALL SIGHT
          OF WHAT WAS IMPORTANT.

42:40.158 --> 42:42.926
              [¶¶¶]

42:51.202 --> 42:53.836
     [MELODIE CRYING SOFTLY]

42:56.741 --> 42:58.675
  AND THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS,
             RIGHT?

43:01.913 --> 43:04.981
              [¶¶¶]

43:08.987 --> 43:10.820
        [CHRISTMAS CAROLS
        PLAYING QUIETLY]

43:10.822 --> 43:11.854
        THAT LOOKS GREAT.

43:11.856 --> 43:13.289
   IT'S JUST A LITTLE UNEVEN.

43:13.291 --> 43:16.092
   MAYBE IF YOU COULD GO GRAB
     ANOTHER ONE? THANK YOU.

43:16.094 --> 43:18.928
  OH, AND THAT SIDE OF THE TREE
     IS A LITTLE BARE, SO...

43:18.930 --> 43:21.130
              [¶¶¶]

43:33.044 --> 43:35.211
           [KNOCKING]

43:38.249 --> 43:39.849
     YOU COULDN'T STAY AWAY.

43:39.851 --> 43:41.784
COULD YOU?

43:49.861 --> 43:53.129
I LOVE MY HUSBAND,
BUT I NEED YOU.

43:53.131 --> 43:55.665
                  DEFINE "NEED."

43:55.667 --> 43:58.334
              SHOW ME... "NEED."

44:11.049 --> 44:13.950
              I'M NOT
              GOING TO SCREW YOU

44:13.952 --> 44:15.284
             WHILE YOU BETRAY ME

44:15.286 --> 44:17.854
      AND HOLD HANDS WITH JORY
      LIKE SOME COOING LOVEBIRD.

44:20.258 --> 44:22.291
        I WANT YOU, BART.

44:23.762 --> 44:26.095
     IT'S BEEN SO LONG SINCE
    I'VE HAD A MAN INSIDE ME.

44:26.097 --> 44:29.298
            YOU REALLY ARE
            A WHORE, AREN'T YOU?

44:29.300 --> 44:30.767
        THE LORD SNAPPED
      YOUR HUSBAND'S SPINE

44:30.769 --> 44:32.201
  AS PUNISHMENT FOR YOUR SINS,

44:32.203 --> 44:34.404
 AND YOU STILL HAVE NOT LEARNED.

44:35.707 --> 44:37.106
                  WHAT'S IT
                  GOING TO TAKE?

44:37.108 --> 44:40.376
          THOSE CREATURES INSIDE
          THAT FAT GUT OF YOURS

44:40.378 --> 44:43.046
             COMING OUT DEFORMED
             AND DEMENTED

44:43.048 --> 44:44.947
          AND DEPRAVED LIKE YOU?

44:44.949 --> 44:46.849
      WELL, THEN WE MIGHT
      AS WELL JUST KILL THEM NOW

44:46.851 --> 44:48.418
         BEFORE THEY'RE RELEASED
         ONTO THIS EARTH.

44:49.921 --> 44:52.088
[BREATH SHUDDERS]

44:52.090 --> 44:55.024
JORY MAY BE CRIPPLED
AND IMPOTENT,

44:55.026 --> 44:57.960
BUT HE'S STILL TEN TIMES
THE MAN YOU'LL EVER BE.

45:03.935 --> 45:06.335
LANCE!
YOU'RE HERE!

45:06.337 --> 45:08.337
AHH! WHOO!

45:09.841 --> 45:12.275
SO BART, LANCE'S DAD

45:12.277 --> 45:14.944
IS THE PRESIDENT OF
CHARTOFF BANKS OF VIRGINIA.

45:14.946 --> 45:17.714
    OH. I'VE DONE QUITE A BIT
   OF BUSINESS WITH CHARTOFF.

45:17.716 --> 45:19.716
THIS IS TRULY
A REMARKABLE PROPERTY

45:19.718 --> 45:21.184
YOU HAVE HERE,
MR. FOXWORTH.

45:21.186 --> 45:22.418
          [CINDY]: OH,
     YOU CAN CALL HIM BART.

45:22.420 --> 45:24.721
    [LANCE]: SOMEDAY, I HOPE
      TO GET MY OWN FORTUNE

45:24.723 --> 45:25.922
         AND GET MYSELF
    A LITTLE PIECE OF HEAVEN

45:25.924 --> 45:27.023
                     LIKE YOURS.

45:27.025 --> 45:28.057
OR YOU COULD
JUST INHERIT IT,

45:28.059 --> 45:29.492
THE WAY
THAT BART DID.

45:30.829 --> 45:32.295
            [LANCE]:
     THAT NETWORKING SYSTEM

45:32.297 --> 45:35.164
         IN YOUR OFFICE
  IS TRULY A SIGHT TO BE SEEN.

45:35.166 --> 45:36.499
     TECHNOLOGY IS THE WAVE
         OF THE FUTURE.

45:36.501 --> 45:38.000
       WOULDN'T YOU AGREE,
          MR. FOXWORTH?

45:38.002 --> 45:39.402
I TOLD YOU
TO CALL HIM BART.

45:39.404 --> 45:42.171
        CINDY, I'M TRYING
        TO BE RESPECTFUL.

45:42.173 --> 45:44.340
     WELL, CINDY HERE CAN BE
A LITTLE ROUGH AROUND THE EDGES.

45:44.342 --> 45:46.843
YOU CAN'T ALWAYS BEAT OUT NATURE
          WITH NURTURE.

45:46.845 --> 45:49.278
AND BART IS JUST
CHARM PERSONIFIED.

45:49.280 --> 45:51.981
       [CATHY]: THIS LAMB
    IS VERY TENDER, ISN'T IT?

45:51.983 --> 45:53.783
       [CHRIS]: DELICIOUS.

45:53.785 --> 45:55.184
    [CINDY]: ALL RIGHT, WELL,
       IF YOU DON'T MIND,

45:55.186 --> 45:57.453
    I THINK I WILL SHOW LANCE
     THE REST OF THE MANOR.

45:57.455 --> 45:59.222
         I PROMISED HIM
        I'D SHOW HIM IT.

45:59.224 --> 46:03.192
      MY PARENTS' QUARTERS
     ARE TO-DIE-FOR, BUT...

46:03.194 --> 46:06.195
      I'M SURE BART'S ROOMS
     ARE THE MOST GORGEOUS.

46:06.197 --> 46:08.998
  I'VE JUST NEVER BEEN INVITED
    TO THE MASTER'S CHAMBERS.

46:09.000 --> 46:10.516
            [LANCE]:
      DINNER WAS WONDERFUL.

46:10.517 --> 46:12.033
        THANKS AGAIN FOR
 YOUR HOSPITALITY, MR. FOXWORTH.

46:12.036 --> 46:13.369
     MR. AND MRS. SHEFFIELD.

46:13.371 --> 46:14.403
YOU'RE WELCOME,
LANCE.

46:14.405 --> 46:16.439
HOW LONG'S
SHE KNOWN HIM?

46:16.441 --> 46:17.874
            [CATHY]:
        OH, ABOUT A WEEK.

46:17.876 --> 46:20.276
              [¶¶¶]

46:22.213 --> 46:25.047
[GASPING AND GROANING]

46:28.987 --> 46:31.053
      [MOANING AND GASPING]

46:32.257 --> 46:34.257
[SHRIEKS]:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

46:36.861 --> 46:39.328
              STOP! YOU'RE GONNA
              KILL HIM! STOP!

46:39.330 --> 46:41.864
          STOP! STOP!
          YOU'RE GONNA KILL HIM!

46:43.434 --> 46:45.902
GOD, I HATE YOU SO MUCH!

46:45.904 --> 46:48.938
     [CINDY]: HE'S A MANIAC,
  AND HE NEEDS TO BE PUT AWAY!

46:48.940 --> 46:50.139
                   HONEY, I KNOW
                   WHAT BART DID

46:50.141 --> 46:51.374
                 WAS DESPICABLE,

46:51.376 --> 46:52.542
          BUT YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE
          SLEPT WITH THAT BOY

46:52.544 --> 46:53.810
                   IN HIS HOUSE.

46:53.811 --> 46:55.077
           YOU KNOW HOW VOLATILE
           YOUR BROTHER IS.

46:55.079 --> 46:56.212
           BART NEARLY
       KILLS MY BOYFRIEND,

46:56.214 --> 46:58.047
             AND YET
    YOU'RE STILL BLAMING ME?

46:58.049 --> 46:59.916
          OKAY, THAT IS NOT WHAT
          I AM SAYING, SWEETIE.

46:59.918 --> 47:01.184
           CAN YOU PLEASE
           HELP ME EXPLAIN THIS?

47:01.186 --> 47:02.385
I DON'T KNOW,
SWEETHEART.

47:02.387 --> 47:04.153
I'M KIND OF
ON CINDY'S SIDE HERE.

47:04.155 --> 47:05.388
            FINALLY!

47:05.390 --> 47:07.490
I THINK BART NEEDS
SOME SERIOUS HELP.

47:07.492 --> 47:09.892
          HE'S JUST STILL UPSET
          ABOUT THE INHERITANCE.

47:09.894 --> 47:12.228
          THE TRICK THAT
          CORINNE PLAYED ON HIM.

47:12.230 --> 47:14.197
               YOU KNOW HOW LONG
               IT TAKES HIM

47:14.199 --> 47:15.832
             TO GET OVER THINGS.

47:15.834 --> 47:17.433
BUT SHE SAID
HE REALLY HURT THAT BOY.

47:17.435 --> 47:19.302
    AND NOW LANCE WON'T EVEN
       TALK TO ME ANYMORE.

47:19.304 --> 47:20.837
                  I KNOW,
                  BUT I'M SAYING

47:20.839 --> 47:21.604
                   THIS IS STILL
                   BART'S HOUSE,

47:21.606 --> 47:23.506
             AND YOU KNOW HOW...

47:23.508 --> 47:25.875
             CONSERVATIVE HE IS.

47:25.877 --> 47:28.544
           AND SWEETIE, YOU ONLY
           JUST MET THIS BOY

47:28.546 --> 47:30.980
               AND YOU'RE HAVING
               SEX WITH HIM?

47:36.120 --> 47:38.120
          [TEARFULLY]:
    I CAN'T HELP MYSELF, MOM.

47:40.425 --> 47:43.259
 IT'S LIKE I HAVE THIS APPETITE,

47:43.261 --> 47:45.628
        AND I CAN'T JUST
        NOT BE WITH A BOY

47:45.630 --> 47:47.330
 AND NOT GIVE HIM WHAT HE WANTS.

47:47.332 --> 47:49.866
          SWEETIE, SEX HAS A WAY
          OF BITING YOU BACK.

47:49.868 --> 47:52.068
          YOU'RE STILL SO YOUNG.
          YOU JUST DON'T KNOW--

47:52.070 --> 47:53.502
I DO KNOW!

47:53.504 --> 47:55.504
    [STAMMERS, THEN SNIFFLES]

47:55.506 --> 47:58.875
          I DON'T KNOW.
            MAYBE...

47:58.877 --> 48:01.244
  MAYBE IF BART DIDN'T GIVE ME
 SUCH A HEAD-TRIP ABOUT MYSELF,

48:01.246 --> 48:03.096
    THEN I WOULDN'T FEEL LIKE

48:03.097 --> 48:04.947
    I HAD TO GIVE MYSELF AWAY
    TO EVERY GUY THAT I MEET.

48:04.949 --> 48:06.249
OH, SWEETHEART.

48:08.353 --> 48:13.022
      THERE ARE BETTER WAYS
      TO VALIDATE YOURSELF.

48:13.024 --> 48:16.425
        AND, SWEETIE,
        I NEVER TOLD YOU THIS...

48:16.427 --> 48:19.262
           BUT I USED MY BODY
           FOR THE WRONG REASONS

48:19.264 --> 48:21.297
             WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.

48:21.299 --> 48:22.565
              I STILL REGRET IT.

48:22.567 --> 48:24.500
      I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
    TO MAKE THE SAME MISTAKE.

48:24.502 --> 48:26.636
YOU GUYS HAVE
SO MANY SECRETS.

48:26.638 --> 48:28.337
I STILL FEEL LIKE

48:28.339 --> 48:30.106
THERE'S SO MUCH
ABOUT YOU I DON'T KNOW.

48:30.108 --> 48:32.608
THERE ARE SOME THINGS
YOU JUST DON'T NEED TO KNOW.

48:32.610 --> 48:35.344
[SMOOCHES HER HEAD]

48:37.115 --> 48:39.215
    THERE ARE SO MANY WHORES
        UNDER THIS ROOF,

48:39.217 --> 48:42.685
    THAT I CAN BARELY BREATHE
THROUGH THE STENCH OF THEIR SIN.

48:42.687 --> 48:45.988
            PLEASE...

48:45.990 --> 48:48.257
      GIVE ME THE STRENGTH
         TO RESIST THEM.

48:51.129 --> 48:54.263
              [¶¶¶]

49:20.959 --> 49:23.392
              I KNOW THAT TRICK.

49:23.394 --> 49:25.428
        WHAT DO YOU WANT?

49:25.430 --> 49:26.529
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

49:26.531 --> 49:27.997
I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY

49:27.999 --> 49:29.398
FOR BEATING UP
YOUR BOY-TOY.

49:29.400 --> 49:32.034
       YOU BROKE HIS NOSE
   IN THREE DIFFERENT PLACES.

49:32.036 --> 49:33.736
           THE BEATING
    WASN'T FUN FOR ME EITHER.

49:33.738 --> 49:35.604
   ALL RIGHT? IT WAS ABSOLUTE
   MURDER ON THE BANK ACCOUNT,

49:35.606 --> 49:37.106
AND RELATIONSHIPS
WITH HIS FATHER.

49:37.108 --> 49:39.075
AND ALL BANTERING ASIDE,
I DO FEEL BAD.

49:39.077 --> 49:41.043
      I NEVER ACTUALLY <i> MEAN</i>
          TO HURT YOU.

49:41.045 --> 49:42.044
          YOU JUST DO.

49:42.046 --> 49:43.179
        YEAH, I GUESS SO.

49:43.181 --> 49:44.547
YOU KNOW,
ALL HE WANTED

49:44.549 --> 49:46.315
WAS TO GET
INTO YOUR PANTS.

49:46.317 --> 49:47.350
                   SEE? THERE
                   YOU GO AGAIN.

49:47.352 --> 49:50.086
I'M SORRY,
BUT YOU'RE--

49:50.088 --> 49:51.620
YOU'RE MY LITTLE SISTER.

49:51.622 --> 49:53.322
I'M ALWAYS GONNA WANT
TO BE PROTECTIVE.

49:53.324 --> 49:55.091
  THAT'S THE FIRST TIME YOU'VE
   EVER CALLED ME YOUR SISTER.

49:55.093 --> 49:57.026
     THAT TRUST-FUND MAGGOT
       DIDN'T DESERVE YOU.

49:57.028 --> 49:59.562
            OH, WELL,
   NOW YOU JUST SOUND JEALOUS.

49:59.564 --> 50:02.031
      DON'T GET IT TWISTED
  LIKE THE REST OF OUR FAMILY.

50:02.033 --> 50:03.165
  WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

50:04.268 --> 50:05.534
      NOTHING. NEVER MIND.

50:05.536 --> 50:09.005
           SO, YOU OFF
      TO GET YOUR DRINK ON?

50:09.007 --> 50:10.272
            CAN I COME WITH YOU?

50:10.274 --> 50:11.674
                I'VE GOT A FAKE,

50:11.675 --> 50:13.075
            AND I CAN PARTY JUST
            AS HARD AS YOU CAN.

50:13.077 --> 50:15.077
         THAT'S EXACTLY
       WHAT I'M SCARED OF.

50:15.079 --> 50:17.146
   WELL, MAYBE IT'S TIME THAT
  YOU STOPPED BEING SO SCARED.

50:17.148 --> 50:19.048
                 MAYBE IT'S TIME

50:19.050 --> 50:21.117
          THAT WE START BEING
          HONEST WITH EACH OTHER

50:21.119 --> 50:22.618
                 ABOUT HOW
                 WE REALLY FEEL.

50:25.323 --> 50:28.090
              [¶¶¶]

50:32.630 --> 50:34.497
     [GASPS] WHAT THE HELL?

50:34.499 --> 50:35.698
   YOU DISGUST ME.

50:35.700 --> 50:37.433
           -SCREW YOU!
       -I'LL PRAY FOR YOU.

50:37.435 --> 50:38.567
  PRAY FOR YOURSELF, DICKHEAD.

50:44.375 --> 50:46.108
                WHAT IS GOING ON
                WITH YOU, BART?

50:46.110 --> 50:47.309
         NOTHING, CHRIS.

50:47.311 --> 50:49.445
        JUST THE USUAL--

50:49.446 --> 50:51.580
  CINDY'S BEING A BITCH-IN-HEAT
       AND I'M BEING A...

50:51.582 --> 50:53.282
           "DICKHEAD."

50:53.284 --> 50:54.550
                    WHY DO
                    YOU DO THAT?

50:54.552 --> 50:56.252
              I'M TRYING TO
              REALLY TALK TO YOU

50:56.254 --> 50:58.554
                   AND YOU JUST
                   PUSH ME AWAY.

50:58.556 --> 50:59.822
                  WE'RE ALL
                  HERE WITH YOU.

50:59.824 --> 51:02.158
               WE COULD BE
               A FAMILY AGAIN...

51:02.160 --> 51:04.293
                   BUT YOU JUST
                   PUSH US AWAY.

51:04.295 --> 51:06.595
          WHY? YOU KNOW,
          I THINK YOU'RE SCARED.

51:06.597 --> 51:08.164
         SCARED THAT WE'RE GONNA
         SEE ALL THOSE THINGS

51:08.166 --> 51:10.132
                YOU HATE SO MUCH
                ABOUT YOURSELF.

51:10.134 --> 51:11.200
                WE ALREADY KNOW
                ALL THOSE THINGS

51:11.202 --> 51:12.368
           ABOUT YOU,

51:12.370 --> 51:14.603
     AND WE STILL LOVE YOU.

51:16.274 --> 51:18.674
              [¶¶¶]

51:19.710 --> 51:21.744
      [MONEY-CLIP CLATTERS]

51:21.746 --> 51:23.379
           THANKS FOR
    THE PSYCHOANALYSIS, DOC.

51:23.381 --> 51:24.647
WHAT DO I OWE YOU?

51:25.716 --> 51:28.317
       YOU DON'T KNOW ME.

51:28.319 --> 51:29.752
             [SMACK]

51:29.754 --> 51:31.287
         YOU DON'T KNOW

51:31.289 --> 51:33.289
        A THING ABOUT ME.

51:33.291 --> 51:35.357
         I RAISED YOU...

51:35.359 --> 51:37.793
           I KNOW YOU.

51:37.795 --> 51:40.329
           AND WHETHER YOU WANT
           TO BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

51:40.331 --> 51:42.798
          WE'RE A LOT MORE ALIKE
          THAN YOU THINK.

51:42.800 --> 51:45.434
      NO, I'M NOT LIKE YOU.
         DO YOU HEAR ME?

51:47.472 --> 51:49.805
     I AM NOTHING LIKE YOU.

51:52.110 --> 51:54.643
              [¶¶¶]

51:57.682 --> 52:00.349
              [¶¶¶]

52:13.297 --> 52:15.331
              [¶¶¶]

52:27.745 --> 52:29.478
             [BART]:
    SEX FOR PLEASURE IS SIN,

52:29.480 --> 52:32.148
  LEADING TO NOTHING BUT PAIN.

52:34.185 --> 52:35.885
    LUST LEADS TO DAMNATION.

52:49.200 --> 52:50.933
                 HOW ARE
                 YOU DOING, MEL?

52:50.935 --> 52:53.435
IT'S LIKE
I'M BEING CONSUMED

52:53.437 --> 52:55.571
BY THIS DARKNESS.

52:57.208 --> 52:58.541
WE ONLY CAME HERE

52:58.543 --> 53:00.376
TO TELL THEM
WE WERE PREGNANT,

53:00.378 --> 53:02.378
SO IF WE DIDN'T HAVE THEM,
WE'D STILL BE DANCING.

53:02.380 --> 53:06.315
THIS HOUSE WANTS TO USE US
TO KEEP IT LIVING ON FOREVER.

53:06.317 --> 53:07.850
   WE DON'T HAVE TO STAY HERE.

53:07.852 --> 53:11.287
             WE-WE--
    WE CAN LEAVE AT ANY TIME.

53:11.289 --> 53:12.788
I'VE BEEN
HAVING NIGHTMARES

53:12.790 --> 53:14.823
THAT THE BABIES
WON'T BE NORMAL

53:14.825 --> 53:17.660
      BECAUSE I HATE THEM.

53:17.662 --> 53:19.828
DON'T SAY THAT.
IT'S NOT TRUE.

53:19.830 --> 53:21.197
                 IT IS!

53:21.199 --> 53:23.599
            I WAS BORN
            TO DANCE BALANCHINE,

53:23.601 --> 53:24.900
             TUDOR AND DE MILLE,

53:24.902 --> 53:27.203
             NOT TO BE A MOTHER!

53:27.205 --> 53:28.470
            YOU WANTED CHILDREN.

53:28.472 --> 53:29.872
                    I DIDN'T.

53:29.874 --> 53:31.307
            I NEVER WANTED THIS.

53:31.309 --> 53:33.676
               [SOBBING]:
               GET IT OUT OF ME.

53:33.678 --> 53:36.612
    GET IT OUT OF ME. GET IT
  OUT OF ME! GET IT OUT OF ME!

53:36.614 --> 53:37.613
               GET IT OUT OF ME!

53:39.717 --> 53:41.383
[SIGHING]

53:41.385 --> 53:43.219
THEY'RE GONNA HAVE TO
KEEP HER SEDATED

53:43.221 --> 53:45.421
SO SHE DOESN'T HURT
HERSELF OR THE BABIES.

53:45.423 --> 53:47.456
IT'S FOR THE BEST.

53:48.726 --> 53:50.693
            COME ON, SON.
            LET'S GO DOWNSTAIRS.

53:53.497 --> 53:55.598
              [¶¶¶]

53:56.734 --> 53:58.801
HERE'S ONE
FOR YOU, CINDY.

53:58.803 --> 54:00.636
                    "FROM BART."

54:02.240 --> 54:03.505
                         [GASPS]

54:03.507 --> 54:04.707
                 OH, MY GOSH.
                 IT'S A DISCMAN!

54:04.709 --> 54:06.775
         I KNOW HOW MUCH
       YOU LOVE YOUR JAMS.

54:06.777 --> 54:08.344
      HOW CAN YOU BE
      A COMPLETE PAIN-IN-THE-ASS

54:08.346 --> 54:09.612
            AND STILL KNOW
            EXACTLY WHAT I WANT?

54:09.614 --> 54:11.447
            THEY SAY
  THE PEOPLE YOU HURT THE MOST

54:11.449 --> 54:13.015
        ARE ALSO THE ONES
       YOU LOVE THE MOST.

54:14.552 --> 54:16.552
               CINDY, WILL YOU
               GRAB THE BIG ONE?

54:16.554 --> 54:17.820
YEAH.

54:17.822 --> 54:19.922
HERE YOU GO, SWEETHEART.

54:23.461 --> 54:25.728
FOR THE MAN
WHO HAS EVERYTHING.

54:29.600 --> 54:30.599
         [PAPER RUSTLES]

54:32.937 --> 54:35.471
             [JORY]:
      I PAINTED IT MYSELF.

54:35.473 --> 54:37.039
JORY, THAT
IS BEAUTIFUL.

54:37.041 --> 54:38.941
   OH, THE HOUSE
   LOOKS SO CREEPY.

54:38.943 --> 54:41.677
I SEE WHY YOU GUYS
WANTED TO RUN AWAY.

54:41.679 --> 54:44.280
           I DON'T THINK IT DOES
           THE HOUSE JUSTICE.

54:44.282 --> 54:45.914
              [¶¶¶]

54:45.916 --> 54:48.284
            A TOAST.

54:48.286 --> 54:49.818
        TO OUR CHILDREN--

54:49.820 --> 54:51.587
         JORY, MELODIE,
          MAY YOUR LOVE

54:51.589 --> 54:53.622
       WITHSTAND THE TEST
       AND TRIALS OF TIME

54:53.624 --> 54:54.723
         LIKE OURS HAS.

54:54.725 --> 54:55.991
        AND BART, CINDY,

54:55.993 --> 54:57.459
        MAY YOU BOTH FIND
  AN ENDURING LOVE OF YOUR OWN.

54:57.461 --> 54:58.961
            -CHEERS.
            -CHEERS.

54:58.963 --> 55:00.663
             [CLINK]

55:00.665 --> 55:02.498
THAT'S REALLY SWEET.

55:02.500 --> 55:03.699
          YEAH, "DAD."

55:03.701 --> 55:05.868
         THAT WAS SWEET.

55:07.004 --> 55:08.003
           AND TRITE.

55:09.340 --> 55:11.807
   AND UNLIKELY FOR ANY OF US.

55:11.809 --> 55:12.908
            I MEAN--

55:12.910 --> 55:14.343
          WELL, I MEAN,
       CINDY HERE JUST...

55:14.345 --> 55:15.811
       JUST GIVES IT AWAY.

55:15.813 --> 55:16.979
            AND I'M--

55:16.981 --> 55:18.947
    I'M AN EMOTIONAL CRIPPLE,
            AND-- OH!

55:18.949 --> 55:20.416
     SPEAKING OF CRIPPLES...

55:20.418 --> 55:21.950
             JORY...

55:21.952 --> 55:23.385
    WELL, HE'S FOUND HIMSELF
            A LYING,

55:23.387 --> 55:24.787
            CHEATING,

55:24.789 --> 55:26.689
       PIECE-OF-TRASH WIFE

55:26.691 --> 55:30.492
 WHO JUST CAN'T SEEM TO STAY OFF
   HER BROTHER-IN-LAW'S JUNK.

55:30.494 --> 55:31.960
          [JORY]: WHAT?

55:31.962 --> 55:33.562
OH, MY GOD.

55:33.564 --> 55:37.966
            [CINDY]:
       YOU ARE A MONSTER.

55:37.968 --> 55:39.335
                          HEY...

55:39.337 --> 55:41.537
                MERRY CHRISTMAS.

55:42.606 --> 55:44.540
            [SPLASH]

55:47.044 --> 55:48.110
   OH, MY GOD.

55:48.112 --> 55:51.447
             -DAD--
    -HER WATER BROKE. CHRIS--

55:51.449 --> 55:53.015
     [CHRIS]: BART, HELP ME
        GET HER UPSTAIRS.

55:58.823 --> 56:00.656
THE AMBULANCE
IS ON ITS WAY!

56:00.658 --> 56:02.358
     IT'S RIPPING ME APART!

56:02.360 --> 56:03.425
      THERE'S NOT GONNA BE
     TIME FOR AN AMBULANCE.

56:03.427 --> 56:05.027
   SON, TAKE THE INSTRUMENTS.

56:05.029 --> 56:07.629
           -[PANTING]
     -DEEP BREATH, AND PUSH.

56:07.631 --> 56:09.398
          [CRYING OUT]

56:09.400 --> 56:10.132
     I SEE THE BABY'S HEAD.
          KEEP PUSHING.

56:10.134 --> 56:11.900
      [GASPING AND PANTING]

56:11.902 --> 56:13.135
         HERE HE COMES!
          KEEP PUSHING.

56:13.137 --> 56:15.804
              AHH!

56:15.806 --> 56:16.772
           IT'S A BOY!

56:16.774 --> 56:17.840
OH!

56:17.842 --> 56:19.908
         HE'S BEAUTIFUL.

56:19.910 --> 56:21.710
            [WHEEZING
      AS HER INFANT CRIES]

56:21.712 --> 56:23.579
            [CATHY]:
        OH! LOOK AT HIM.

56:24.648 --> 56:27.082
                HERE'S YOUR SON.

56:28.953 --> 56:31.854
        [GASPS SUDDENLY]

56:31.856 --> 56:32.955
OKAY. OKAY.

56:32.957 --> 56:34.423
     HIS TWIN'S ON ITS WAY!

56:34.425 --> 56:36.692
        OH! NO! OH, STOP!

56:36.694 --> 56:37.993
      ONE MORE TIME FOR ME.
       I NEED YOU TO PUSH.

56:37.995 --> 56:39.094
        [EXHALES DEEPLY]

56:39.096 --> 56:40.662
           HERE COMES YOUR BABY.

56:42.967 --> 56:44.633
       [GASPING INTENSELY]

56:44.635 --> 56:45.834
             IT'S A LITTLE GIRL.

56:47.438 --> 56:48.470
            [CATHY]:
        A BOY AND A GIRL?

56:48.472 --> 56:49.471
             [CRIES]

56:53.577 --> 56:55.077
           HERE WE GO.

57:00.518 --> 57:02.117
   YOU ARE GONNA HAVE THE LIFE

57:02.119 --> 57:04.620
      THAT CORY AND CARRIE
         SHOULD'VE HAD.

57:04.622 --> 57:06.622
         HEY. [GIGGLES]

57:07.691 --> 57:10.125
              [¶¶¶]

57:17.668 --> 57:21.069
YOU COULDN'T GO
WITHOUT IT FOR THREE MONTHS?

57:24.775 --> 57:26.074
                      I'M SORRY.

57:26.076 --> 57:27.943
          I DIDN'T KNOW
        WHAT I WAS DOING.

57:27.945 --> 57:31.213
              I WAS COMING APART
              AT THE SEAMS...

57:31.215 --> 57:34.016
               AND HE WAS THERE.

57:38.489 --> 57:41.023
              ARE YOU
              GOING TO LEAVE ME?

57:42.493 --> 57:45.027
I DON'T KNOW.

57:46.697 --> 57:48.630
               [WHIMPERS SOFTLY]

57:54.839 --> 57:58.106
         [CATHY]: HELLO,
    MY PRECIOUS LITTLE ONES.

57:58.108 --> 58:01.109
      YOU ARE SO BEAUTIFUL.

58:01.111 --> 58:03.812
HOW AM I GOING TO
TAKE CARE OF TWO BABIES

58:03.814 --> 58:05.814
AND JORY
ALL BY MYSELF?

58:07.685 --> 58:09.918
        DON'T UNDERESTIMATE HIM.

58:11.255 --> 58:12.955
    JORY IS GOING TO BE ABLE

58:12.957 --> 58:16.492
   TO DO EVERYTHING ANY OTHER
   ABLE-BODIED FATHER CAN DO.

58:17.828 --> 58:19.528
   AND CHRIS AND I WILL HELP.

58:19.530 --> 58:21.497
                WE'LL HIRE MAIDS
                AND NANNIES.

58:21.499 --> 58:23.499
              GOOD.

58:26.003 --> 58:27.936
      BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
       IF I'M GOING TO BE

58:27.938 --> 58:29.972
A VERY
HANDS-ON MOTHER.

58:31.842 --> 58:33.609
       YOU'RE JUST SCARED.

58:33.611 --> 58:35.110
          YOUR MATERNAL INSTINCT
          WILL KICK IN

58:35.112 --> 58:37.179
             AND YOU'LL BE FINE.

58:40.684 --> 58:42.818
              [¶¶¶]

58:45.523 --> 58:47.823
                       JORY, W--

58:50.594 --> 58:53.228
[STRAINING INTENSELY]

58:53.230 --> 58:55.163
             [GASPS]

59:01.805 --> 59:04.673
             JORY...

59:04.675 --> 59:06.241
          I'M GONNA GO
       CHECK ON THE TWINS.

59:06.243 --> 59:08.243
WE NEED TO TALK.

59:09.947 --> 59:11.613
LEAVE US.

59:11.615 --> 59:12.781
         ALL THIS TIME,

59:12.783 --> 59:15.918
            I THOUGHT
     WE WERE BECOMING CLOSER

59:15.920 --> 59:18.554
         AND YOU'VE BEEN
     SLEEPING WITH MY WIFE.

59:18.556 --> 59:20.055
           THEN AGAIN,
     SHE WAS PREGNANT AND--

59:20.057 --> 59:22.024
       AND I'M PARALYZED,

59:22.026 --> 59:23.191
                    SO HOW COULD
                    YOU RESIST?

59:23.193 --> 59:25.127
SHE WAS A WRECK
AFTER THE ACCIDENT, OKAY?

59:25.129 --> 59:26.929
SHE CAME TO ME.

59:26.931 --> 59:28.697
   THAT'S HARDLY LIKE MELODIE.

59:28.699 --> 59:30.165
         SHE HAS MORALS.

59:30.167 --> 59:31.600
                I WAS HER FIRST!

59:31.602 --> 59:33.135
YOU'RE SO BLIND.

59:33.137 --> 59:36.305
SHE LUSTS AND DECEIVES
LIKE ALL WOMEN.

59:36.307 --> 59:38.607
IF YOU THINK
SHE CAN BE TRUSTED,

59:38.609 --> 59:41.243
THEN... YOU'RE A FOOL.

59:41.245 --> 59:43.078
            IT'S YOU
      WHO CAN'T BE TRUSTED.

59:43.080 --> 59:44.613
                    YOU MAY HAVE
                    GROWN UP,

59:44.615 --> 59:45.647
               BUT YOU ARE STILL

59:45.649 --> 59:47.950
              THE SAME
              TORTURED, WOUNDED,

59:47.952 --> 59:50.252
           FRIENDLESS LITTLE BOY
           YOU ALWAYS WERE!

59:50.254 --> 59:52.721
   IT'S NO WONDER GRANDMOTHER
      LEFT YOU EVERYTHING.

59:52.723 --> 59:54.189
       YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
         IN THIS FAMILY

59:54.191 --> 59:56.758
      THAT'S AS SCREWED UP
           AS SHE WAS!

59:57.795 --> 01:00:00.128
        [CHAIR WHIRRING]

01:00:00.130 --> 01:00:02.598
              [¶¶¶]

01:00:08.305 --> 01:00:11.840
        [INFANTS CRYING]

01:00:25.022 --> 01:00:27.356
              MEL?

01:00:32.696 --> 01:00:35.063
         MEL? YOU HERE?

01:00:52.783 --> 01:00:57.285
¶ THERE'S GONNA BE HELL TO PAY ¶

01:00:57.287 --> 01:01:01.256
  ¶ AT THE END OF YOUR DAY... ¶

01:01:01.258 --> 01:01:06.895
              [¶¶¶]

01:01:16.707 --> 01:01:18.306
              JORY?

01:01:18.308 --> 01:01:20.342
       HONEY, WHAT IS IT?

01:01:21.945 --> 01:01:23.912
         [INFANT CRIES]

01:01:26.884 --> 01:01:29.251
SHE'S GONE.

01:01:30.421 --> 01:01:32.721
SHE JUST... LEFT ME.

01:01:32.723 --> 01:01:34.723
AND THE BABIES.

01:01:38.295 --> 01:01:42.130
       WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
ABANDONS HER-- HER OWN CHILDREN?

01:01:44.768 --> 01:01:47.335
              [¶¶¶]

01:01:49.006 --> 01:01:50.939
   [MUSIC FILTERING FROM BAR]

01:01:54.378 --> 01:01:57.279
      [INDISTINCT CHUCKLING
          AND CHATTING]

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:16.865
              [¶¶¶]

01:02:16.867 --> 01:02:18.934
BART!

01:02:18.936 --> 01:02:20.402
 YOU SCARED THE HELL OUT OF ME.
       WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:02:20.404 --> 01:02:21.903
                 I COULD ASK YOU
                 THE SAME THING.

01:02:21.905 --> 01:02:23.772
          YOU'RE TOO YOUNG TO BE
          GOING TO BARS, CINDY.

01:02:23.774 --> 01:02:25.073
 ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME, STALKER?

01:02:25.075 --> 01:02:27.976
DID YOU LIKE
WHAT YOU SAW?

01:02:27.978 --> 01:02:29.778
       DID IT GET YOU OFF?

01:02:31.882 --> 01:02:34.182
  STOP TRYING TO INTIMIDATE ME,
       BECAUSE YOU DON'T.

01:02:34.184 --> 01:02:36.451
    WHEN WILL YOU ADMIT THAT
    YOU ARE OBSESSED WITH ME,

01:02:36.453 --> 01:02:38.920
   AND THAT IT INFURIATES YOU
   TO SEE ME WITH ANOTHER MAN?

01:02:38.922 --> 01:02:40.889
    BART! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
       BART! PUT ME DOWN!

01:02:40.891 --> 01:02:42.290
         BART! STOP IT!

01:02:42.292 --> 01:02:45.193
       BART, LET GO OF ME!
          PUT ME DOWN!

01:02:46.330 --> 01:02:48.163
[GASPS]

01:02:48.165 --> 01:02:49.831
WHAT?

01:02:49.833 --> 01:02:51.967
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO?

01:02:53.070 --> 01:02:55.303
              [¶¶¶]

01:03:12.322 --> 01:03:16.224
THAT IS ONE CREEPY PAINTING
OF GREAT-GRANDFATHER MALCOLM.

01:03:16.226 --> 01:03:18.960
            YOU'RE NOT PERMITTED
            IN MY QUARTERS.

01:03:18.962 --> 01:03:23.064
     WELL... I JUST FIGURED,
      SINCE AFTER TONIGHT--

01:03:23.066 --> 01:03:25.000
               NOTHING
               HAPPENED TONIGHT,

01:03:25.002 --> 01:03:26.101
               AND IT WILL NEVER
               HAPPEN AGAIN.

01:03:26.103 --> 01:03:27.235
                  DO YOU
                  UNDERSTAND ME?

01:03:27.237 --> 01:03:28.403
      WE DON'T HAVE TO DENY

01:03:28.405 --> 01:03:29.871
          THE FEELINGS
  THAT WE FEEL FOR EACH OTHER.

01:03:29.873 --> 01:03:31.223
ALL MY LIFE,

01:03:31.224 --> 01:03:32.574
YOU MADE ME FEEL ASHAMED
FOR BEING ADOPTED,

01:03:32.576 --> 01:03:35.076
BUT NOW
I'M SO HAPPY I AM,

01:03:35.078 --> 01:03:36.912
  'CAUSE, I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE
        WE'RE BLOOD SIBS,

01:03:36.914 --> 01:03:37.913
        LIKE MOM AND DAD.

01:03:39.016 --> 01:03:40.081
YEAH, I KNOW.

01:03:40.083 --> 01:03:41.449
    I WAS BOUND TO FIGURE OUT

01:03:41.451 --> 01:03:44.186
 ABOUT THEIR INSANELY DISTURBING
       SECRET EVENTUALLY.

01:03:44.188 --> 01:03:47.088
  THEIR SIN IS RUNNING THROUGH
    OUR VEINS LIKE WILDFIRE.

01:03:49.860 --> 01:03:51.426
     I CAN'T STOP IT, CAN I?

01:03:53.063 --> 01:03:54.429
IT'S NOT A SIN.

01:03:54.431 --> 01:03:56.531
           NOT FOR US.

01:03:57.835 --> 01:03:59.901
NOT REALLY.

01:04:03.106 --> 01:04:05.073
            -[GASPS]
      -GET ON YOUR KNEES--

01:04:05.075 --> 01:04:07.509
            ...WHORE,
   AND PRAY TO SAVE YOUR SOUL.

01:04:08.579 --> 01:04:10.278
          [CINDY SOBS]

01:04:13.217 --> 01:04:15.217
 [CATHY]: WHY DO YOU HAVE TO GO
           RIGHT NOW?

01:04:15.219 --> 01:04:17.018
 [CINDY]: I JUST HAVE TO LEAVE.
           THAT'S ALL.

01:04:17.020 --> 01:04:20.088
I UNDERSTAND THAT,
BUT WHAT ABOUT SCHOOL?

01:04:20.090 --> 01:04:22.057
YOU WERE SO EXCITED
TO START IN THE SPRING.

01:04:22.059 --> 01:04:25.026
            YOU KNOW,
 I'M NOT REALLY THE SCHOOL TYPE,

01:04:25.028 --> 01:04:26.862
 AND I WAS JUST DOING IT BECAUSE
IT'S WHAT YOU GUYS WANTED ME TO.

01:04:26.864 --> 01:04:28.096
     BUT EVERYBODY HAS DONE

01:04:28.098 --> 01:04:30.198
  THE WHOLE DANCER-IN-NEW-YORK
             THING,

01:04:30.200 --> 01:04:32.634
       SO THIS IS MY TURN.

01:04:32.636 --> 01:04:34.202
         OKAY, SWEETIE,

01:04:34.204 --> 01:04:35.570
      SHOULDN'T WE AT LEAST
     TALK ABOUT THIS FIRST?

01:04:35.572 --> 01:04:37.105
            I CAN'T.
I'M GONNA BE LATE FOR MY FLIGHT.

01:04:37.107 --> 01:04:39.140
   WELL, CINDY, WE CAN CHANGE
      YOUR FLIGHT. PLEASE?

01:04:41.945 --> 01:04:43.945
            I CAN'T.

01:04:43.947 --> 01:04:46.548
   I CAN'T STAY ANOTHER MINUTE
    IN THE HOUSE OF MALCOLM.

01:04:46.550 --> 01:04:49.150
               WELL, BREAK A LEG
               OUT THERE.

01:04:49.152 --> 01:04:51.453
       [CAB ENGINE STARTS]

01:04:57.227 --> 01:04:59.227
            LET'S GO.

01:05:05.002 --> 01:05:07.569
 [CHRIS]: I THINK HE'S STARTING
     TO LOSE CONTROL AGAIN.

01:05:07.571 --> 01:05:10.138
                 HE WAS DOING
                 SO WELL BEFORE.

01:05:10.140 --> 01:05:13.208
       YOU KNOW, HONESTLY,
   I THINK IT'S US BEING HERE.

01:05:13.210 --> 01:05:15.310
       OR ME.

01:05:15.312 --> 01:05:18.213
    I THINK HE'S STARTING TO
     SLIP BACK AND REGRESS.

01:05:18.215 --> 01:05:19.915
                  WE CAN'T
                  LEAVE HIM NOW.

01:05:19.917 --> 01:05:21.383
          NOT WHILE HE NEEDS US.

01:05:21.385 --> 01:05:23.585
     WE WON'T.

01:05:23.587 --> 01:05:26.087
       I'LL START LOOKING
       FOR HOUSES NEARBY.

01:05:26.089 --> 01:05:27.422
            THAT WAY,
     HE CAN HAVE HIS SPACE,

01:05:27.424 --> 01:05:29.324
         AND WE'LL STILL
      BE AVAILABLE FOR HIM.

01:05:31.295 --> 01:05:34.029
                     OKAY.

01:05:34.031 --> 01:05:35.964
         [TONI]: YOU TWO
       ARE THE BEST BABIES

01:05:35.966 --> 01:05:37.999
    I'VE EVER TAKEN CARE OF.

01:05:39.636 --> 01:05:42.304
           [GRUNTING]

01:05:42.306 --> 01:05:43.405
          HERE YOU GO.

01:05:43.407 --> 01:05:45.373
          THANKS, TONI.

01:05:45.375 --> 01:05:47.676
        I DON'T KNOW HOW
   I EVER MANAGED WITHOUT YOU.

01:05:47.678 --> 01:05:49.411
            THE BABIES LOVE YOU.
            I LOVE YOU.

01:05:49.413 --> 01:05:51.313
I'VE BEEN...

01:05:51.315 --> 01:05:55.317
   WAITING FOR THE RIGHT TIME
    TO TELL YOU THIS, BUT...

01:05:55.319 --> 01:05:57.218
         I'M A BIG FAN.

01:05:57.220 --> 01:05:59.054
WHEN I HEARD
ABOUT YOUR ACCIDENT,

01:05:59.056 --> 01:06:01.222
I WAS DEVASTATED.

01:06:01.224 --> 01:06:03.291
      I'M AT PEACE WITH IT.

01:06:03.293 --> 01:06:05.560
      NOW I HAVE NO EXCUSE
  NOT TO START CHOREOGRAPHING,

01:06:05.562 --> 01:06:07.329
   LIKE I ALWAYS TALKED ABOUT.

01:06:07.331 --> 01:06:10.198
     [TONI]: WELL, I WILL BE
   AT YOUR FIRST PERFORMANCE.

01:06:13.403 --> 01:06:15.303
     YEAH, I'M WELL AWARE OF
  THE DECLINES IN STOCK PRICES,

01:06:15.305 --> 01:06:16.738
     BUT WHAT I NEED TO TALK
        TO YOU ABOUT IS--

01:06:16.740 --> 01:06:19.374
    HERE. HOLD THAT THOUGHT.
I'LL GET-- I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

01:06:23.647 --> 01:06:26.147
                            HEY.

01:06:26.149 --> 01:06:28.750
            HOW'S IT GOING WITH
            THE LITTLE RUG-RATS?

01:06:28.752 --> 01:06:30.485
   GREAT.

01:06:30.487 --> 01:06:34.556
DARREN IS ALL SMILES

01:06:34.558 --> 01:06:36.758
AND DIERDRE'S TAKING
EVERYTHING IN LIKE A SLEUTH.

01:06:36.760 --> 01:06:38.159
     YEAH, THAT DIERDRE HAS

01:06:38.161 --> 01:06:40.295
    QUITE A PENETRATING GAZE,
          DOESN'T SHE?

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:45.233
     [CHUCKLES]

01:06:45.235 --> 01:06:46.601
     BET YOU HAVE A WAY WITH
       KIDS, MR. FOXWORTH.

01:06:46.603 --> 01:06:49.004
           AH, JUST--
          CALL ME BART.

01:06:50.207 --> 01:06:52.707
           OKAY. BART.

01:06:53.777 --> 01:06:56.077
              [¶¶¶]

01:07:02.119 --> 01:07:04.686
              [¶¶¶]

01:07:04.688 --> 01:07:09.157
   HANDS BACK... AND FORWARD.

01:07:09.159 --> 01:07:11.126
         [TONI CHUCKLES]

01:07:12.396 --> 01:07:15.397
              [¶¶¶]

01:07:37.187 --> 01:07:38.319
                   YOU TREAT
                   YOUR VEHICLES

01:07:38.321 --> 01:07:40.755
                  LIKE THEY WERE
                  YOUR CHILDREN.

01:07:40.757 --> 01:07:43.291
         THESE BAD BOYS
    ARE MY BABIES, ALL RIGHT.

01:07:45.362 --> 01:07:47.729
            YOU KNOW,
  IN THE NOT-SO-DISTANT FUTURE,

01:07:47.731 --> 01:07:51.266
    I COULD SEE MYSELF HAVING
  THE FLESH-AND-BLOOD VARIETY.

01:07:51.268 --> 01:07:53.802
            ARE YOU THINKING
            ABOUT MARRYING TONI?

01:07:55.138 --> 01:07:56.671
           I KNOW YOU
      AND CHRIS WERE HOPING

01:07:56.673 --> 01:07:58.573
        THAT SHE AND JORY
        MIGHT HIT IT OFF,

01:07:58.575 --> 01:08:01.209
    BUT SHE FELL FOR ME, MOM.

01:08:01.211 --> 01:08:03.678
     SHE CHOSE ME OVER JORY.

01:08:03.680 --> 01:08:05.113
 HONEY, IT'S NOT A COMPETITION.

01:08:05.115 --> 01:08:06.214
            ISN'T IT?

01:08:06.216 --> 01:08:08.083
WELL, HE ALWAYS
SEEMS TO WIN.

01:08:08.085 --> 01:08:10.285
          WITH MELODIE,
    I WAS JUST A SUBSTITUTE,

01:08:10.287 --> 01:08:11.753
         BUT WITH TONI,

01:08:11.755 --> 01:08:13.721
          I COME FIRST.

01:08:16.460 --> 01:08:18.660
        WELL, AS LONG AS

01:08:18.662 --> 01:08:21.362
      YOU'RE BOTH DOING IT
     FOR THE RIGHT REASONS.

01:08:21.363 --> 01:08:23.298
WHY? WHAT, YOU THINK
SHE ONLY LOVES ME

01:08:23.300 --> 01:08:24.866
BECAUSE I'M GOING TO HAVE
MORE MONEY THAN GOD?

01:08:24.868 --> 01:08:27.202
  HONEY, I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
       REMOTELY LIKE THAT.

01:08:27.203 --> 01:08:28.536
 DO YOU THINK I'M GOOD-LOOKING?

01:08:28.537 --> 01:08:30.604
     I THINK ALL MY CHILDREN
         ARE BEAUTIFUL.

01:08:30.607 --> 01:08:31.840
  THAT'S NOT AN ANSWER, MOTHER!

01:08:33.210 --> 01:08:35.777
      BART, I THINK YOU ARE
       A BEAUTIFUL PERSON,

01:08:35.779 --> 01:08:37.779
               AND I THINK
               YOU DESERVE LOVE,

01:08:37.781 --> 01:08:39.848
                 WITH OR WITHOUT
                 YOUR MONEY.

01:08:41.885 --> 01:08:44.452
AND NOW I HAVE IT.

01:08:45.622 --> 01:08:46.787
     WITH TONI.

01:08:51.461 --> 01:08:53.728
                 WELL, I'M HAPPY
                 FOR YOU BOTH.

01:08:55.265 --> 01:08:57.765
              [¶¶¶]

01:09:03.305 --> 01:09:05.807
       [MALCOLM'S VOICE]:
      <i> IT IS GREED AND LUST</i>

01:09:05.809 --> 01:09:07.642
     <i> THAT DRIVES ALL WOMEN.</i>

01:09:07.644 --> 01:09:09.444
    <i> AND IT IS THEIR GUILEFUL</i>
       <i> POWER OF DECEPTION</i>

01:09:09.446 --> 01:09:10.845
     <i> THAT SUBDUES A MAN...</i>

01:09:13.817 --> 01:09:15.850
    <i> ...AND MAKES HIM BELIEVE</i>
      <i> IN CHILDISH NOTIONS</i>

01:09:15.852 --> 01:09:18.786
    <i> OF LOVE AND DEVOTION...</i>

01:09:18.787 --> 01:09:21.156
       <i> ...AND COMMITMENT.</i>

01:09:22.526 --> 01:09:24.792
             [GASPS]

01:09:28.430 --> 01:09:29.564
I DON'T UNDERSTAND

01:09:29.566 --> 01:09:31.698
WHY YOU'RE
TELLING ME THIS NOW.

01:09:31.701 --> 01:09:34.769
I FEEL LIKE WE'RE JUST
STARTING SOMETHING SPECIAL,

01:09:34.770 --> 01:09:36.203
AND YOU'RE TRYING
TO DRIVE ME AWAY.

01:09:36.206 --> 01:09:39.240
    I HAVE BEEN DAMAGED GOODS
          ALL MY LIFE.

01:09:40.377 --> 01:09:42.210
          MY TWO-FACED
      SOW OF A GRANDMOTHER

01:09:42.212 --> 01:09:43.645
   DID TIME IN A CRAZY HOUSE,

01:09:43.647 --> 01:09:46.180
  AND SHE KNEW THAT IS EXACTLY
        WHERE I'D END UP.

01:09:46.183 --> 01:09:48.683
      I MEAN, SHE EVEN PUT
    A STIPULATION IN HER WILL

01:09:48.685 --> 01:09:50.585
    THAT, IF I GOT PUT AWAY,
      I'D LOSE EVERYTHING.

01:09:50.587 --> 01:09:51.886
   LIKE SOME KIND OF PROPHECY.

01:09:51.888 --> 01:09:54.756
       I DON'T CARE ABOUT
        YOUR MONEY, BART.

01:09:54.758 --> 01:09:56.724
    ALL I CARE ABOUT IS YOU.

01:09:56.726 --> 01:09:57.692
   DON'T LIE TO ME, YOU BITCH.

01:09:58.828 --> 01:10:00.828
           I'VE SEEN HOW
           YOU LOOK AT MY HOUSE,

01:10:00.830 --> 01:10:02.597
           MY THINGS,

01:10:02.599 --> 01:10:04.532
        ENJOYING THIS...

01:10:04.534 --> 01:10:07.235
     EASY LIFE YOU HAVE JUST
     WEASELED YOUR WAY INTO.

01:10:07.237 --> 01:10:08.770
         YOUR GONNA HAVE TO FIND
         SOME OTHER RICH FOOL

01:10:08.772 --> 01:10:09.938
        TO SPREAD YOUR LEGS FOR,

01:10:09.940 --> 01:10:12.840
           BECAUSE I CAN'T STAND
           THE SIGHT OF YOU.

01:10:14.444 --> 01:10:16.878
              [¶¶¶]

01:10:22.419 --> 01:10:24.419
              TONI?

01:10:25.555 --> 01:10:27.855
              [¶¶¶]

01:10:46.943 --> 01:10:48.977
[SHUTS ENGINE OFF]

01:10:55.252 --> 01:10:56.484
              HI, DR. SHEFFIELD.

01:10:56.486 --> 01:10:57.652
HELLO.

01:10:57.654 --> 01:10:59.754
          SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

01:10:59.756 --> 01:11:01.689
IT LOOKS GOOD.

01:11:01.691 --> 01:11:04.392
 THE FRONT IS WIDE ENOUGH FOR US
 TO PUT IN A WHEELCHAIR ACCESS.

01:11:04.394 --> 01:11:05.677
                AND THE HALLWAYS
                INSIDE

01:11:05.678 --> 01:11:06.961
              ARE WIDE ENOUGH
              FOR YOUR SON, TOO.

01:11:06.963 --> 01:11:07.929
GREAT.
LET'S TAKE A LOOK.

01:11:07.931 --> 01:11:09.664
                          RIGHT.

01:11:09.666 --> 01:11:11.866
              [¶¶¶]

01:11:27.417 --> 01:11:29.484
   "YOUR PRESENCE IS REQUESTED

01:11:29.486 --> 01:11:31.386
         FOR THE SERVICE
   AT THE FOXWORTH HALL CHAPEL

01:11:31.388 --> 01:11:32.687
          THIS SUNDAY.

01:11:32.689 --> 01:11:35.423
   WELCOME, AND THANK YOU ALL
      FOR JOINING ME TODAY.

01:11:35.425 --> 01:11:38.693
   AT THIS, OUR FIRST SERVICE
  AT THE FOXWORTH HALL CHAPEL,

01:11:38.695 --> 01:11:41.596
        I'D LIKE TO HONOR
   THIS MOMENTOUS OCCASION...

01:11:41.598 --> 01:11:45.033
         BY WELCOMING...

01:11:45.035 --> 01:11:47.502
       THE NEWEST MEMBERS
         OF OUR FAMILY--

01:11:47.504 --> 01:11:50.438
            DARREN...
      AND DIERDRE MARQUET.

01:11:55.312 --> 01:11:58.346
             WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:12:00.850 --> 01:12:03.384
      AHH. LITTLE DIERDRE.

01:12:05.622 --> 01:12:08.856
    NOW, IF YOU WOULD PLEASE
JOIN ME IN BAPTIZING THIS CHILD.

01:12:08.858 --> 01:12:09.991
BART, I DON'T
THINK WE SHOULD.

01:12:09.993 --> 01:12:12.660
            WHY NOT?

01:12:12.662 --> 01:12:13.828
        DON'T YOU WANT TO
         SAVE HER SOUL?

01:12:16.566 --> 01:12:19.600
              [¶¶¶]

01:12:24.708 --> 01:12:27.442
             LORD...

01:12:27.444 --> 01:12:30.478
      OUR MERCIFUL FATHER,

01:12:30.480 --> 01:12:32.113
PLEASE FULFIL YOUR PROMISE TO US

01:12:32.115 --> 01:12:35.383
     AND RECEIVE THIS CHILD
        INTO YOUR KINGDOM

01:12:35.385 --> 01:12:37.618
           AS A MEMBER
       OF YOUR OWN FAMILY.

01:12:37.620 --> 01:12:38.753
            GRANT...

01:12:38.755 --> 01:12:40.888
      THAT THEY MAY RECEIVE

01:12:40.890 --> 01:12:43.024
  THE FULLNESS OF YOUR GRACE...

01:12:43.026 --> 01:12:46.394
              [¶¶¶]

01:12:46.396 --> 01:12:49.130
        PURIFYING HER...

01:12:49.132 --> 01:12:50.498
             EVIL--

01:12:51.835 --> 01:12:53.768
         -DISGUSTING...
        -[WATER BUBBLING]

01:12:53.770 --> 01:12:55.136
         -...VILE SINS.

01:12:55.138 --> 01:12:57.138
            -[CRIES]
   -BART! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:12:58.775 --> 01:13:01.109
        [DIERDRE CRYING]

01:13:01.111 --> 01:13:02.577
    [ECHOING]: WHAT THE HELL
         WERE YOU DOING?

01:13:02.579 --> 01:13:03.644
       SHE'S JUST A BABY!

01:13:03.646 --> 01:13:05.947
           I'M SORRY.

01:13:07.517 --> 01:13:09.016
   I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

01:13:09.018 --> 01:13:10.084
KNOW THIS--

01:13:10.086 --> 01:13:11.552
IF I EVER CATCH YOU

01:13:11.554 --> 01:13:13.087
EVEN <i> LOOKING</i>
AT MY KIDS AGAIN,

01:13:13.089 --> 01:13:14.088
         I'LL KILL YOU!

01:13:14.090 --> 01:13:15.523
DO YOU HEAR ME?

01:13:23.933 --> 01:13:26.000
I'M SORRY, MOM.

01:13:26.002 --> 01:13:28.102
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT CAME OVER ME.

01:13:28.104 --> 01:13:29.637
             IT'S OKAY, SWEETIE.

01:13:29.639 --> 01:13:31.672
           YOU JUST HAVEN'T BEEN
           TAKING YOUR PILLS,

01:13:31.674 --> 01:13:33.408
                  HAVE YOU, HUH?

01:13:33.410 --> 01:13:35.176
                   THERE YOU GO.

01:13:44.554 --> 01:13:47.588
              NOW YOU TRY TO GET
              SOME SLEEP, OKAY?

01:13:47.590 --> 01:13:50.057
       YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
   THAT'S EVER CARED ABOUT ME.

01:13:50.059 --> 01:13:52.059
                THAT'S NOT TRUE.

01:13:52.061 --> 01:13:53.861
            EVERYBODY LOVES YOU.

01:13:53.863 --> 01:13:56.664
            YOUR FATHER WOULD
            DO ANYTHING FOR YOU.

01:13:57.801 --> 01:13:59.834
HE'S NOT MY FATHER.

01:14:04.874 --> 01:14:07.508
OKAY. I JUST THINK
WE SHOULD LET HIM REST

01:14:07.510 --> 01:14:08.709
AND WE CAN TALK TO HIM
ABOUT IT IN THE MORNING.

01:14:08.711 --> 01:14:10.178
      HE NEEDS HELP, CATHY.

01:14:10.180 --> 01:14:11.846
         ARE YOU SAYING
      WE SHOULD COMMIT HIM?

01:14:11.848 --> 01:14:13.748
 WE CAN'T DO THAT TO HIM AGAIN.

01:14:13.750 --> 01:14:15.216
 MOM, HE NEARLY DROWNED DIERDRE.

01:14:15.218 --> 01:14:17.852
        I KNOW, I JUST...

01:14:19.122 --> 01:14:21.856
    I DON'T WANT HIM TO THINK
   THERE'S NO ONE ON HIS SIDE.

01:14:21.858 --> 01:14:23.891
              OKAY.

01:14:23.893 --> 01:14:26.160
     BUT WE'RE NOT SPENDING
  ANOTHER NIGHT IN THIS HOUSE.

01:14:26.162 --> 01:14:28.563
        I'LL GO FINALIZE
        THE RENTAL HOME,

01:14:28.565 --> 01:14:30.765
   AND I WANT EVERYBODY PACKED
     BY THE TIME I GET HOME.

01:14:30.767 --> 01:14:32.033
     I JUST DON'T FEEL RIGHT

01:14:32.035 --> 01:14:33.768
       ABOUT SNEAKING OFF
        AND LEAVING HIM--

01:14:33.770 --> 01:14:35.503
       HE'S LOST IT, MOM.
        WE NEED TO THINK

01:14:35.505 --> 01:14:37.572
        OF THE CHILDREN.

01:14:46.916 --> 01:14:49.050
              [¶¶¶]

01:14:51.154 --> 01:14:53.821
          [PHONE RINGS]

01:14:56.893 --> 01:14:58.092
             HELLO?

01:14:58.094 --> 01:14:59.560
        WE GOT THE HOUSE.
        I'M HEADED BACK.

01:14:59.562 --> 01:15:01.762
      OKAY. HE'S STILL OUT,

01:15:01.764 --> 01:15:03.498
        BUT I DON'T KNOW
      FOR HOW MUCH LONGER.

01:15:03.499 --> 01:15:05.233
       JUST MAKE SURE JORY
    AND TONI ARE READY TO GO.

01:15:05.235 --> 01:15:06.934
    <i> I'LL BE HOME SOON, OKAY?</i>

01:15:06.936 --> 01:15:08.169
        OKAY. I LOVE YOU.

01:15:08.171 --> 01:15:09.637
  I LOVE YOU, TOO, SWEETHEART.

01:15:13.009 --> 01:15:15.209
              [¶¶¶]

01:15:19.148 --> 01:15:20.748
LEAVING SO SOON,<i> MOM?</i>

01:15:20.750 --> 01:15:22.884
              [¶¶¶]

01:15:30.026 --> 01:15:31.959
        IT'S ALMOST TIME.
    WE SHOULD WAKE THE TWINS.

01:15:37.534 --> 01:15:39.700
HI. YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:15:39.702 --> 01:15:42.003
 HEY. I TOOK THE TURN TOO QUICK,
       I BLEW MY TIRE OUT.

01:15:42.005 --> 01:15:44.038
    YEAH, I'VE SEEN A LOT OF
     ACCIDENTS AT THIS TURN.

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:45.172
       YOU NEED SOME HELP?

01:15:45.174 --> 01:15:46.541
             PLEASE.

01:15:46.543 --> 01:15:48.576
I'M JUST GONNA PULL UP.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

01:15:54.784 --> 01:15:57.718
              [¶¶¶]

01:16:00.690 --> 01:16:02.924
         [BABIES COOING]

01:16:02.926 --> 01:16:05.259
          [TENSE SIGH]

01:16:07.130 --> 01:16:09.297
              [¶¶¶]

01:16:12.869 --> 01:16:14.802
                  [PANTING]

01:16:15.872 --> 01:16:18.205
            YOU'RE FORSAKING ME?

01:16:18.207 --> 01:16:19.574
              -WHY?
              -NO.

01:16:19.576 --> 01:16:21.175
I'VE TRIED TO HELP YOU,

01:16:21.177 --> 01:16:23.277
BUT I CAN'T DO IT
ANYMORE, BART. I CAN'T.

01:16:23.279 --> 01:16:24.812
     YOU'RE LEAVING ME HERE.

01:16:24.814 --> 01:16:26.047
                    ALONE.

01:16:26.049 --> 01:16:27.615
          YOU'RE ALONE
      BECAUSE YOU PUSH AWAY

01:16:27.617 --> 01:16:28.683
    EVERYBODY WHO LOVES YOU--

01:16:28.685 --> 01:16:30.218
                NO, IT'S BECAUSE

01:16:30.219 --> 01:16:31.752
  YOU ARE CHOOSING YOUR BROTHER
       OVER ME, ISN'T IT?

01:16:31.754 --> 01:16:32.887
             NO. NO!

01:16:32.889 --> 01:16:34.255
            ISN'T IT?

01:16:36.826 --> 01:16:38.259
             SAY IT.

01:16:40.196 --> 01:16:42.997
         [VOICE BREAKS]:
    I'M CHOOSING MY BROTHER.

01:16:44.233 --> 01:16:46.701
          YOU CHOOSE...

01:16:47.737 --> 01:16:48.836
            TO BURN.

01:16:48.838 --> 01:16:50.805
                     KNEEL DOWN.

01:16:53.710 --> 01:16:57.011
              [¶¶¶]

01:16:57.013 --> 01:16:58.846
        [BREATH SHAKING]

01:16:58.848 --> 01:17:00.081
      TAKE OFF YOUR SHIRT.

01:17:00.083 --> 01:17:01.182
              WHAT?

01:17:01.184 --> 01:17:02.149
             [GASPS]

01:17:02.151 --> 01:17:04.085
                          DO IT.

01:17:04.087 --> 01:17:06.721
       OKAY. OKAY. OKAY...

01:17:06.723 --> 01:17:08.189
       [HYPERVENTILATING]

01:17:08.191 --> 01:17:09.390
        YOU BROUGHT THIS
     UPON YOURSELF, MOTHER.

01:17:14.831 --> 01:17:16.998
             [GASPS]

01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:19.367
              [¶¶¶]

01:17:22.705 --> 01:17:25.406
       YOU ARE THE SOURCE

01:17:25.408 --> 01:17:27.775
       OF ALL THAT'S EVIL
         IN THIS FAMILY.

01:17:27.777 --> 01:17:29.243
                    MALCOLM SAYS

01:17:29.245 --> 01:17:32.113
            THAT YOU NEED TO
            SUFFER FOR YOUR SINS

01:17:32.115 --> 01:17:33.914
     IN ORDER FOR ALL OF US
         TO BE PURIFIED.

01:17:33.916 --> 01:17:35.282
        MALCOLM IS DEAD.

01:17:35.284 --> 01:17:37.652
  HE'S BEEN DEAD FOR 40 YEARS.

01:17:37.654 --> 01:17:38.953
                             NO!

01:17:38.955 --> 01:17:42.356
          HE'S CRAWLING
 IN EVERY CORNER OF THIS HOUSE,

01:17:42.358 --> 01:17:44.959
    IN EVERY CELL OF MY BODY.

01:17:44.961 --> 01:17:47.194
  YOU NEED HELP...

01:17:47.196 --> 01:17:49.397
         BART.

01:17:51.300 --> 01:17:54.802
           OF COURSE
           THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

01:17:54.804 --> 01:17:56.904
           TO HAVE ME COMMITTED,

01:17:56.906 --> 01:17:59.373
                 SO THAT YOU
                 AND UNCLE CHRIS

01:17:59.375 --> 01:18:01.742
             CAN TAKE EVERYTHING
             AWAY FROM ME!

01:18:01.744 --> 01:18:03.344
         YOU AND CORINNE
 PLANNED IT FROM THE BEGINNING.

01:18:03.346 --> 01:18:04.779
         NO!

01:18:04.781 --> 01:18:05.913
    NO, WE DIDN'T.

01:18:05.915 --> 01:18:07.314
       I SWEAR,

01:18:07.316 --> 01:18:10.384
I HAD NO IDEA
WHAT SHE WAS UP TO.

01:18:10.386 --> 01:18:12.820
              [¶¶¶]

01:18:13.956 --> 01:18:16.957
        THERE'S NO BLOOD
      LIKE FAMILY'S BLOOD.

01:18:18.061 --> 01:18:20.294
       AT THE END OF DAYS,

01:18:20.296 --> 01:18:22.430
        THEY ARE THE ONES
       WHO CAN DESTROY US

01:18:22.432 --> 01:18:24.999
       IF WE DO NOT PURIFY
      THEIR TAINTED BLOOD.

01:18:25.001 --> 01:18:26.367
          [DOOR OPENS]

01:18:26.369 --> 01:18:27.702
                           BART!

01:18:27.704 --> 01:18:29.170
          [JORY GRUNTS
        AND CATHY GASPS]

01:18:31.274 --> 01:18:33.441
         [BOTH GRUNTING]

01:18:37.113 --> 01:18:39.113
                  JORY! STOP IT!

01:18:40.183 --> 01:18:42.083
          GET OFF HIM!
          JORY, PLEASE!

01:18:43.252 --> 01:18:44.852
[GRUNTS]

01:18:44.854 --> 01:18:47.088
       [SPUTTERING AND COUGHING]

01:18:47.090 --> 01:18:48.355
                         GO! GO!

01:18:52.428 --> 01:18:53.894
            [PANTING]

01:18:53.896 --> 01:18:55.863
          I DON'T KNOW
      WHY YOU KEEP THINKING

01:18:55.865 --> 01:18:56.964
        HE'LL GET BETTER.

01:18:56.966 --> 01:18:58.132
                  HE NEVER WILL.

01:18:58.134 --> 01:19:00.101
         HE'S HOPELESS!

01:19:01.237 --> 01:19:03.003
[BART WHEEZES]

01:19:03.005 --> 01:19:05.406
     MALCOLM MADE ME DO IT.

01:19:06.809 --> 01:19:09.143
   TO SAVE THE FOXWORTH NAME.
     HE MADE ME DO IT, MOM.

01:19:11.013 --> 01:19:13.180
          [SOBS SOFTLY]

01:19:18.521 --> 01:19:20.454
          I'M LEAVING.

01:19:21.991 --> 01:19:24.258
          NO. NO. MOM.

01:19:24.260 --> 01:19:25.493
         MOM!

01:19:25.495 --> 01:19:28.162
    MOM...

01:19:28.164 --> 01:19:30.765
PLEASE DON'T GO.
ALL RIGHT?

01:19:30.767 --> 01:19:33.200
I'LL CHANGE.
I PROMISE.

01:19:35.004 --> 01:19:37.204
                I'M SORRY.

01:19:39.475 --> 01:19:41.442
          [BART WEEPS]

01:19:42.512 --> 01:19:43.878
              MOM?

01:19:43.880 --> 01:19:46.247
   PLEASE DON'T LEAVE ME HERE.

01:19:48.151 --> 01:19:51.786
          [CRIES OUT]:
   PLEASE DON'T LEAVE ME HERE!

01:19:51.788 --> 01:19:53.788
             [SOBS]

01:19:54.891 --> 01:19:56.824
         [CHRIS GRUNTS]

01:19:56.826 --> 01:19:58.559
           ALL RIGHT,
     I THINK THAT'LL DO 'ER.

01:19:58.561 --> 01:20:00.394
                THANK YOU AGAIN.

01:20:00.396 --> 01:20:02.029
  I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD'VE
   DONE IF YOU HADN'T STOPPED.

01:20:02.031 --> 01:20:04.431
IT'S ALL RIGHT. WE ALL NEED
A LITTLE HELP SOMETIMES.

01:20:04.433 --> 01:20:05.833
        [TIRES SQUEALING]

01:20:11.507 --> 01:20:13.307
        HE SHOULD BE HERE
             BY NOW.

01:20:13.309 --> 01:20:16.177
          I'M A TERRIBLE MOTHER.

01:20:17.580 --> 01:20:19.580
          I'M JUST LIKE CORINNE.

01:20:24.020 --> 01:20:26.320
                      HE'S HERE!

01:20:28.257 --> 01:20:30.291
    [CATHY SIGHS AND SNIFFS]

01:20:34.030 --> 01:20:36.263
              [¶¶¶]

01:20:45.274 --> 01:20:48.075
     [CINDY STARTS SOBBING]

01:20:50.346 --> 01:20:51.846
                 I CAN'T BELIEVE
                 HE'S GONE.

01:20:53.282 --> 01:20:55.883
              [¶¶¶]

01:21:00.489 --> 01:21:02.523
  WE WERE MEANT FOR EACH OTHER.

01:21:05.595 --> 01:21:07.628
              [¶¶¶]

01:21:20.977 --> 01:21:23.010
         I'VE ALWAYS KNOWN THAT.

01:21:24.146 --> 01:21:27.114
              [¶¶¶]

01:21:32.154 --> 01:21:36.190
        [JORY]: YOU WERE
  THE MAN THAT I ASPIRED TO BE.

01:21:36.192 --> 01:21:38.058
        I LOVE YOU, DAD.

01:21:39.195 --> 01:21:41.428
              [¶¶¶]

01:22:00.082 --> 01:22:02.283
      IT SAYS IN <i> THE BIBLE,</i>

01:22:02.285 --> 01:22:05.452
     "FOR WHATEVER ONE SOWS,
    THAT WILL HE ALSO REAP."

01:22:07.189 --> 01:22:09.089
      "FOR THE ONE WHO SOWS
        TO HIS OWN FLESH

01:22:09.091 --> 01:22:11.425
  WILL FROM THE FLESH REAP..."

01:22:11.427 --> 01:22:14.094
   [RAIN PATTERING UMBRELLAS]

01:22:17.166 --> 01:22:19.366
  I HAD A DIFFICULT CHILDHOOD.

01:22:22.371 --> 01:22:24.371
               NO.

01:22:25.441 --> 01:22:28.575
          NO, I WAS...
       A DIFFICULT CHILD.

01:22:30.079 --> 01:22:32.212
         AND NOW I'M NOT
       A VERY NICE PERSON.

01:22:32.214 --> 01:22:34.181
       CHRIS ONCE ASKED ME

01:22:34.183 --> 01:22:36.317
     WHY I PUSH PEOPLE AWAY,
             AND...

01:22:38.721 --> 01:22:41.455
         [VOICE BREAKS]:
    I DON'T REALLY KNOW WHY.

01:22:46.429 --> 01:22:48.262
 BUT HE WAS ALWAYS THERE FOR ME,

01:22:48.264 --> 01:22:51.732
    NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
      I PUSHED HIM AWAY...

01:22:55.104 --> 01:22:56.603
            [SNIFFS]

01:22:56.605 --> 01:22:59.573
       UNTIL I FINALLY DID
         PUSH HIM AWAY.

01:23:01.610 --> 01:23:04.311
         I DON'T WANT TO
    PUSH PEOPLE AWAY ANYMORE.

01:23:06.315 --> 01:23:08.615
    I DON'T WANT TO BE ALONE.

01:23:10.987 --> 01:23:13.387
        I'M SORRY, CHRIS.

01:23:15.691 --> 01:23:17.725
              [¶¶¶]

01:23:37.480 --> 01:23:39.179
      [CATHY]: <i> AND FINALLY,</i>

01:23:39.181 --> 01:23:40.647
    <i> THE DOLLANGANGER FAMILY</i>

01:23:40.649 --> 01:23:46.186
     <i> WAS FREE FROM THE HOLD</i>
      <i> OF THIS AWFUL HOUSE.</i>

01:23:46.188 --> 01:23:47.321
                            BYE!

01:23:47.323 --> 01:23:48.555
BYE, MOM.

01:23:54.296 --> 01:23:58.165
       [CATHY]: <i> AND OUT OF</i>
  <i> ITS IMPRISONING DARKNESS...</i>

01:23:58.167 --> 01:24:00.367
       <i> AND INTO THE LIGHT</i>

01:24:00.369 --> 01:24:02.436
      <i> OF A NEW BEGINNING.</i>

01:24:06.342 --> 01:24:08.609
         YOUR AWARENESS
 OF EACH OTHER'S SPACE ON STAGE

01:24:08.611 --> 01:24:10.911
          IS FANTASTIC.

01:24:10.912 --> 01:24:13.212
    [CATHY]: <i> AND MY CHILDREN</i>
     <i> WERE ABLE TO FLOURISH.</i>

01:24:13.215 --> 01:24:14.615
       NOW WE ARE GOING TO
      CHASE THE DEVIL AWAY!

01:24:14.617 --> 01:24:15.682
        PRAISE THE LORD.

01:24:15.684 --> 01:24:17.518
        AND YOU ALL KNOW
        MY BEAUTIFUL WIFE

01:24:17.520 --> 01:24:19.720
 AND PARTNER-IN-JESUS... CINDY?

01:24:19.722 --> 01:24:21.221
           COME ON UP.
       [CROWD APPLAUDING]

01:24:21.223 --> 01:24:23.223
PRAISE THE LORD!

01:24:23.225 --> 01:24:24.975
      THERE YOU GO, HONEY.

01:24:24.976 --> 01:24:26.726
      NOW, LET US REMEMBER
   THAT A LOVE JUST LIKE THIS

01:24:26.729 --> 01:24:29.096
      COULD NOT BE POSSIBLE
    IF IT WERE NOT FOR JESUS.

01:24:30.633 --> 01:24:33.600
              [¶¶¶]

01:24:33.602 --> 01:24:36.570
      [CATHY]: <i> MY CHILDREN</i>
   <i> WANTED ME TO GO WITH THEM</i>

01:24:36.572 --> 01:24:39.373
        <i> SO WE COULD ALL</i>
        <i> STAY TOGETHER...</i>

01:24:39.375 --> 01:24:41.575
          <i> AS A FAMILY.</i>

01:24:43.579 --> 01:24:46.346
 <i> BUT, AS MUCH AS I WANTED TO...</i>

01:24:46.348 --> 01:24:48.715
           <i> I DIDN'T.</i>

01:24:48.717 --> 01:24:51.218
    <i> I NEEDED TO STAY HERE...</i>

01:24:53.222 --> 01:24:55.522
       <i> IN FOXWORTH HALL.</i>

01:25:03.666 --> 01:25:06.800
        <i> EVERYTHING I AM</i>
     <i> IS TIED TO THIS HOUSE.</i>

01:25:09.105 --> 01:25:11.105
           <i> MY LIFE...</i>

01:25:11.107 --> 01:25:13.207
           <i> MY LOVE...</i>

01:25:15.411 --> 01:25:18.112
   <i> AND, WITHOUT CHRISTOPHER,</i>

01:25:18.114 --> 01:25:20.647
         <i> I AM A SHADOW</i>
       <i> OF MY FORMER SELF.</i>

01:25:23.652 --> 01:25:25.686
            <i> A GHOST.</i>

01:25:29.625 --> 01:25:33.794
          <i> THE LAST OF</i>
   <i> THE FOUR "DRESDEN DOLLS."</i>

01:25:35.197 --> 01:25:37.397
              [¶¶¶]

01:25:44.273 --> 01:25:49.409
  <i> PEOPLE USE THE COLOR YELLOW</i>
       <i> TO SYMBOLIZE HOPE.</i>

01:25:49.411 --> 01:25:51.545
           <i> YELLOW...</i>

01:25:51.547 --> 01:25:53.547
  <i> LIKE THE SUN WE RARELY SAW.</i>

01:25:55.684 --> 01:25:58.218
  <i> LIFE THEN WAS SO HOPELESS...</i>

01:26:00.556 --> 01:26:04.158
     <i> WE NEVER MADE EVEN ONE</i>
  <i> OF OUR PAPER FLOWERS YELLOW.</i>

01:26:04.160 --> 01:26:06.393
              [¶¶¶]

01:26:17.373 --> 01:26:19.640
 <i> BUT ALL COLORS FADE WITH TIME.</i>

01:26:21.610 --> 01:26:24.278
     <i> MUCH LIKE MEMORIES DO.</i>

01:26:25.614 --> 01:26:27.848
         <i> THEY SOFTEN...</i>

01:26:27.850 --> 01:26:30.284
           <i> AND FADE.</i>

01:26:32.655 --> 01:26:33.820
         <i> AND YELLOW...</i>

01:26:35.791 --> 01:26:39.927
     <i> LEAVING ROOM FOR HOPE.</i>

01:26:42.331 --> 01:26:47.234
              [¶¶¶]
